<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> skos:scopeNote '''kinematics in 1D and 2D; Newton's laws of motion; work, energy, and power; conservation of energy and momentum; rotational motion and torque; simple harmonic motion; gravitation; fluid statics and dynamics''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-classical-mechanics-inertia> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''inertia''' ;
  skos:definition '''The tendency of an object to resist changes in its state of motion, quantified by mass.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-classical-mechanics-momentum> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''momentum''' ;
  skos:definition '''The product of an object's mass and velocity, p = mv; a conserved quantity in isolated systems.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-classical-mechanics-impulse> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''impulse''' ;
  skos:definition '''The change in momentum of an object, equal to the net force integrated over the time interval it acts.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-classical-mechanics-torque> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''torque''' ;
  skos:definition '''The rotational analog of force, defined as the cross product of the position vector and the applied force: τ = r × F.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-classical-mechanics-moment-of-inertia> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''moment of inertia''' ;
  skos:definition '''The rotational analog of mass; measures a body's resistance to angular acceleration: I = sum(m_i * r_i^2).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-classical-mechanics-angular-momentum> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''angular momentum''' ;
  skos:definition '''The rotational analog of linear momentum: L = I * ω = r × p; conserved when net torque is zero.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-classical-mechanics-center-of-mass> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''center of mass''' ;
  skos:definition '''The mass-weighted average position of all particles in a system; the system behaves as if all its mass is concentrated there under external forces.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-classical-mechanics-conservative-force> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''conservative force''' ;
  skos:definition '''A force whose work done on a particle moving between two points is independent of the path taken; derivable from a potential energy function.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-classical-mechanics-simple-harmonic-motion> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''simple harmonic motion''' ;
  skos:definition '''Oscillatory motion governed by a restoring force proportional to displacement: F = -kx, producing sinusoidal position as a function of time.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-classical-mechanics-escape-velocity> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''escape velocity''' ;
  skos:definition '''The minimum speed required for an object to escape a gravitational field without further propulsion: v_esc = sqrt(2GM/r).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-classical-mechanics-bernoulli-s-principle> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Bernoulli's principle''' ;
  skos:definition '''Along a streamline in steady, incompressible, inviscid flow, the sum of pressure, kinetic energy density, and gravitational potential energy density is constant.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-classical-mechanics-reynolds-number> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Reynolds number''' ;
  skos:definition '''A dimensionless ratio Re = ρvL/μ characterizing whether flow is laminar or turbulent.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-classical-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-physics-classical-mechanics-kinematic-equation-constant-acceleration> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''kinematic equation (constant acceleration)''' ;
