<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> skos:scopeNote '''Coulomb's law and electric field; Gauss's law; electric potential and capacitance; magnetic forces and Biot-Savart law; Ampère's law and Faraday's law; Maxwell's equations (integral and differential); electromagnetic waves and Poynting vector; boundary conditions and wave reflection/transmission; multipole expansion; radiation from accelerating charges''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-electromagnetism-electric-field> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''electric field''' ;
  skos:definition '''A vector field E(r) such that the force on a test charge q is F = qE; created by charges and time-varying magnetic fields.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-electromagnetism-electric-potential> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''electric potential''' ;
  skos:definition '''A scalar field V(r) such that E = -∇V; the work done per unit charge moving from infinity to the point r.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-electromagnetism-gauss-s-law> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Gauss's law''' ;
  skos:definition '''The total electric flux through a closed surface equals the enclosed charge divided by ε_0: ∮ E · dA = Q_enc/ε_0.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-electromagnetism-faraday-s-law> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Faraday's law''' ;
  skos:definition '''A time-varying magnetic flux through a loop induces an EMF equal to minus the rate of change of flux: EMF = -dΦ_B/dt.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-electromagnetism-amp-re-maxwell-law> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Ampère-Maxwell law''' ;
  skos:definition '''The curl of B equals μ_0 times the sum of free current density and the displacement current density ε_0 ∂E/∂t.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-electromagnetism-displacement-current> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''displacement current''' ;
  skos:definition '''Maxwell's addition to Ampère's law: J_d = ε_0 ∂E/∂t; ensures charge conservation and predicts electromagnetic wave propagation in vacuum.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-electromagnetism-poynting-vector> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Poynting vector''' ;
  skos:definition '''S = (1/μ_0) * E × B; represents the directional energy flux density of an electromagnetic field (power per unit area).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-electromagnetism-electromagnetic-wave> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''electromagnetic wave''' ;
  skos:definition '''A self-sustaining oscillation of coupled E and B fields propagating at speed c = 1/sqrt(ε_0 μ_0) in vacuum; E and B are perpendicular to each other and to the direction of propagation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-electromagnetism-magnetic-vector-potential> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''magnetic vector potential''' ;
  skos:definition '''A vector field A such that B = ∇ × A; used with scalar potential φ to encode the full EM field in Lagrangian/quantum treatments.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-electromagnetism-lenz-s-law> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Lenz's law''' ;
  skos:definition '''The induced EMF always acts to oppose the change in magnetic flux that produced it; a consequence of energy conservation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-electromagnetism-boundary-conditions-em> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''boundary conditions (EM)''' ;
  skos:definition '''At an interface: tangential E and normal B are continuous; tangential H and normal D jump by the surface free current/charge densities.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-electromagnetism-skin-depth> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''skin depth''' ;
  skos:definition '''The characteristic depth δ = sqrt(2/(μ σ ω)) at which electromagnetic fields penetrate a conductor before attenuating by 1/e.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-electromagnetism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-physics-electromagnetism-coulomb-s-law> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Coulomb's law''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''F = (1/(4*pi*epsilon_0)) * q_1*q_2/r^2  (r̂ direction)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''law''' ;
