<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-quantum-mechanics-hermitian-operator> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Hermitian operator''' ;
  skos:definition '''An operator Â satisfying Â† = Â; its eigenvalues are real and eigenvectors form a complete orthonormal basis, making it suitable to represent a physical observable.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-quantum-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-quantum-mechanics-commutator> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''commutator''' ;
  skos:definition '''For operators Â and B̂, [Â,B̂] = ÂB̂ - B̂Â; non-zero commutator means the observables cannot be simultaneously specified with arbitrary precision.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-quantum-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-quantum-mechanics-heisenberg-uncertainty-principle> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Heisenberg uncertainty principle''' ;
  skos:definition '''For conjugate variables position and momentum: σ_x * σ_p ≥ ℏ/2; a consequence of the non-commutativity [x̂, p̂] = iℏ.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-quantum-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-quantum-mechanics-stationary-state> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''stationary state''' ;
  skos:definition '''An eigenstate of the Hamiltonian Ĥ|E_n> = E_n|E_n>; its probability density is time-independent.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-quantum-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-quantum-mechanics-ladder-operators> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''ladder operators''' ;
  skos:definition '''Operators â and â† defined for the harmonic oscillator by â = (x̂ + ip̂/mω)/sqrt(2mωℏ) and its conjugate; â†|n> = sqrt(n+1)|n+1>, â|n> = sqrt(n)|n-1>.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-quantum-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-quantum-mechanics-spin> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''spin''' ;
  skos:definition '''An intrinsic angular momentum of a quantum particle with no classical analogue; spin-1/2 particles have eigenvalues ±ℏ/2 and are described by Pauli matrices.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-quantum-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-quantum-mechanics-pauli-matrices> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Pauli matrices''' ;
  skos:definition '''Three 2×2 Hermitian matrices σ_x, σ_y, σ_z representing the spin-1/2 operators (up to ℏ/2); satisfy σ_i σ_j = δ_ij I + i ε_ijk σ_k.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-quantum-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-quantum-mechanics-time-evolution-operator> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''time evolution operator''' ;
  skos:definition '''The unitary operator Û(t,t_0) = exp(-iĤ(t-t_0)/ℏ) for time-independent Ĥ; propagates states forward: |ψ(t)> = Û(t,t_0)|ψ(t_0)>.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-quantum-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-quantum-mechanics-fermi-s-golden-rule> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Fermi's golden rule''' ;
  skos:definition '''The transition rate from state |i> to states |f> under perturbation H' is Γ = (2π/ℏ)|<f|H'|i>|^2 * ρ(E_f); valid to first-order time-dependent perturbation theory.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-quantum-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-quantum-mechanics-variational-principle> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''variational principle''' ;
  skos:definition '''For any normalized trial state |φ>, <φ|Ĥ|φ> ≥ E_0 (the true ground-state energy); enables upper-bound estimates of E_0.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-quantum-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-quantum-mechanics-wkb-approximation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''WKB approximation''' ;
  skos:definition '''A semiclassical approximation valid when the de Broglie wavelength changes slowly; the wave function in a slowly varying potential is ψ ~ exp(±i ∫ p(x) dx/ℏ)/sqrt(p(x)).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-quantum-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-quantum-mechanics-scattering-cross-section> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''scattering cross section''' ;
  skos:definition '''The effective area σ that characterizes the probability of a scattering event; differential cross section dσ/dΩ = |f(θ,φ)|^2 where f is the scattering amplitude.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-quantum-mechanics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-physics-quantum-mechanics-time-dependent-schr-dinger-equation> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''time-dependent Schrödinger equation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''iℏ * ∂ψ/∂t = Ĥψ = (-ℏ^2/(2m) ∇^2 + V)ψ''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
