<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> skos:scopeNote '''equivalence principle; curved spacetime and metric tensor; geodesics and Christoffel symbols; Riemann and Ricci tensors; Ricci scalar; Einstein field equations; weak-field limit and Newtonian gravity; Schwarzschild solution and black holes; gravitational waves; cosmological models (FRW metric, Friedmann equations)''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-general-relativity-equivalence-principle> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''equivalence principle''' ;
  skos:definition '''Locally, a uniformly accelerating frame is indistinguishable from a gravitational field (Einstein's version); gravity is not a force but geometry.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-general-relativity-metric-tensor> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''metric tensor''' ;
  skos:definition '''The symmetric tensor g_{μν}(x) encoding the geometry of spacetime; defines the line element ds^2 = g_{μν} dx^μ dx^ν and hence distances, angles, and time elapsed.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-general-relativity-geodesic> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''geodesic''' ;
  skos:definition '''The generalization of a straight line to curved spacetime; the path of a free-falling particle (no non-gravitational forces) that extremizes proper time.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-general-relativity-christoffel-symbol> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Christoffel symbol''' ;
  skos:definition '''Γ^λ_{μν} = (1/2)g^{λσ}(∂_μ g_{νσ} + ∂_ν g_{μσ} - ∂_σ g_{μν}); the connection coefficients encoding parallel transport on the curved manifold.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-general-relativity-riemann-curvature-tensor> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Riemann curvature tensor''' ;
  skos:definition '''R^λ_{ρμν} = ∂_μ Γ^λ_{νρ} - ∂_ν Γ^λ_{μρ} + Γ^λ_{μσ}Γ^σ_{νρ} - Γ^λ_{νσ}Γ^σ_{μρ}; measures the failure of parallel transport around a closed loop.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-general-relativity-ricci-tensor> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Ricci tensor''' ;
  skos:definition '''R_{μν} = R^λ_{μλν}; the contraction of the Riemann tensor that appears in the Einstein field equations.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-general-relativity-einstein-tensor> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Einstein tensor''' ;
  skos:definition '''G_{μν} = R_{μν} - (1/2)g_{μν}R; divergence-free (∇^μ G_{μν} = 0), consistent with energy-momentum conservation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-general-relativity-stress-energy-tensor> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''stress-energy tensor''' ;
  skos:definition '''T_{μν} encodes the density and flux of energy and momentum; T^{00} = energy density, T^{0i} = momentum density; the source of gravity in GR.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-general-relativity-schwarzschild-radius> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Schwarzschild radius''' ;
  skos:definition '''r_s = 2GM/c^2; the radius at which the Schwarzschild metric becomes singular; the event horizon of a non-rotating black hole.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-general-relativity-event-horizon> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''event horizon''' ;
  skos:definition '''A null hypersurface beyond which events cannot causally influence the exterior; in the Schwarzschild metric, located at r = r_s = 2GM/c^2.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-general-relativity-gravitational-wave> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''gravitational wave''' ;
  skos:definition '''A propagating perturbation h_{μν} = g_{μν} - η_{μν} of spacetime geometry, sourced by time-varying quadrupole mass distributions; travels at c and carries energy.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-general-relativity-cosmological-constant> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''cosmological constant''' ;
  skos:definition '''Λ, Einstein's term added to the field equations representing a constant energy density of vacuum; currently interpreted as dark energy driving accelerated expansion.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-general-relativity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
