<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-thermodynamics-classical> skos:scopeNote '''zeroth and first laws; heat, work, and internal energy; ideal gas law and kinetic theory; entropy and the second law; Carnot cycle and thermodynamic efficiency; heat engines and refrigerators; thermodynamic processes (isothermal, adiabatic, isochoric, isobaric)''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-thermodynamics-classical-thermal-equilibrium> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''thermal equilibrium''' ;
  skos:definition '''Two systems are in thermal equilibrium if they share the same temperature and no net heat flows between them; basis of the zeroth law.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-thermodynamics-classical> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-thermodynamics-classical-internal-energy> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''internal energy''' ;
  skos:definition '''The total microscopic kinetic and potential energy of a system's constituent particles; a state function whose change equals heat added minus work done by the system.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-thermodynamics-classical> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-thermodynamics-classical-adiabatic-process> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''adiabatic process''' ;
  skos:definition '''A thermodynamic process in which no heat is exchanged with the surroundings (Q = 0); for an ideal gas: PV^γ = constant where γ = C_P/C_V.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-thermodynamics-classical> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-thermodynamics-classical-heat-capacity> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''heat capacity''' ;
  skos:definition '''The energy required to raise the temperature of a substance by one degree: C = δQ/dT; at constant volume C_V = (∂U/∂T)_V; at constant pressure C_P = (∂H/∂T)_P.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-thermodynamics-classical> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-thermodynamics-classical-carnot-efficiency> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Carnot efficiency''' ;
  skos:definition '''The maximum efficiency of any heat engine operating between reservoirs at T_H and T_C: η_Carnot = 1 - T_C/T_H; achieved only by a reversible engine.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-thermodynamics-classical> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-thermodynamics-classical-entropy-classical> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''entropy (classical)''' ;
  skos:definition '''A state function defined by dS = δQ_rev/T for reversible processes; always increases in irreversible processes in an isolated system (second law).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-thermodynamics-classical> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-thermodynamics-classical-equation-of-state> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''equation of state''' ;
  skos:definition '''A relation among the thermodynamic state variables (e.g., P, V, T, N) of a system; the ideal gas law PV = nRT is the simplest example.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-thermodynamics-classical> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-thermodynamics-classical-specific-heat-ratio> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''specific heat ratio''' ;
  skos:definition '''γ = C_P/C_V; for ideal monatomic gas γ = 5/3; diatomic γ = 7/5; determines the slope of adiabats and the speed of sound.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-thermodynamics-classical> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-physics-thermodynamics-classical-ideal-gas-law> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''ideal gas law''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''P*V = n*R*T = N*k_B*T''' ;
