<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics> skos:scopeNote '''vector calculus: gradient, divergence, curl, Stokes/Gauss theorems; complex analysis and contour integration; ordinary differential equations: power series solutions, Frobenius method; special functions: Legendre, Bessel, Hermite, Laguerre; Fourier series and Fourier transforms; Laplace transform; linear algebra: eigenvalues, diagonalization; tensors and index notation; Green's functions''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics-gradient> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''gradient''' ;
  skos:definition '''∇f = (∂f/∂x, ∂f/∂y, ∂f/∂z); a vector pointing in the direction of maximum rate of increase of scalar field f.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics> ;
