  skos:prefLabel '''curl''' ;
  skos:definition '''∇×F; a vector field whose magnitude and direction encode the circulation per unit area of F; appears in Faraday's and Ampère's laws.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics-dirac-delta-function> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Dirac delta function''' ;
  skos:definition '''A generalized function δ(x-a) = 0 for x≠a and ∫ δ(x-a)f(x)dx = f(a); used to represent point sources and initial conditions.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics-green-s-function> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Green's function''' ;
  skos:definition '''G(x,x') satisfying L G(x,x') = δ(x-x') for linear operator L; enables solutions to inhomogeneous equations as y(x) = ∫ G(x,x') f(x') dx'.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics-legendre-polynomials> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Legendre polynomials''' ;
  skos:definition '''P_l(cos θ) are solutions to Legendre's equation arising in azimuthally symmetric problems (e.g., multipole expansion, hydrogen atom); orthogonal on [-1,1].''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics-bessel-functions> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Bessel functions''' ;
  skos:definition '''J_n(x) and Y_n(x) are solutions to Bessel's equation, arising in cylindrical symmetry problems; J_n is regular at the origin, Y_n diverges there.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics-fourier-transform> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Fourier transform''' ;
  skos:definition '''f̃(k) = ∫ f(x) exp(-ikx) dx; decomposes a function into its frequency components; inverse: f(x) = (1/2π) ∫ f̃(k) exp(ikx) dk.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics-residue-theorem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''residue theorem''' ;
  skos:definition '''∮_C f(z) dz = 2πi * sum(residues inside C); allows evaluation of real integrals by closing contours in the complex plane.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-physics-mathematical-methods-in-physics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
