  skos:prefLabel '''Diels-Alder reaction''' ;
  skos:definition '''A [4+2] cycloaddition between a conjugated diene (4 pi electrons) and a dienophile (2 pi electrons) to form a six-membered ring; syn-addition, endo rule.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-organic-reactions-and-mechanisms> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-organic-reactions-and-mechanisms-enol-enolate> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''enol / enolate''' ;
  skos:definition '''An enol is a tautomer of a carbonyl compound with OH on a sp2 carbon; an enolate is its conjugate base, a resonance-stabilized carbanion.''' ;
