<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions> skos:scopeNote '''Boltzmann distribution and the canonical ensemble; Partition function q: translational, rotational, vibrational, electronic contributions; Relationship between partition function and thermodynamic quantities (U, S, A, G, C_V); Equipartition theorem and heat capacities of ideal gases; Grand canonical and microcanonical ensembles; Residual entropy: degeneracy at 0 K; Molecular symmetry numbers in rotational partition functions; Absolute entropy calculation from spectroscopic data''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions-partition-function-q-or-z> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''partition function (q or Z)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The sum over all quantum states of the Boltzmann factor: q = sum_i exp(-E_i / k_B T); encodes all thermodynamic information of a system.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions-boltzmann-distribution> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Boltzmann distribution''' ;
  skos:definition '''The probability of a system being in state i: P_i = exp(-E_i / k_B T) / q.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions-canonical-ensemble> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''canonical ensemble''' ;
  skos:definition '''A statistical mechanical ensemble of systems at fixed N, V, and T; the partition function is Q = q^N / N! for distinguishable or indistinguishable particles.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions-equipartition-theorem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''equipartition theorem''' ;
  skos:definition '''Each quadratic term in the classical Hamiltonian contributes (1/2)k_B T to the mean energy; translational and rotational modes each contribute (3/2)k_B T (linear), vibrational at high T contributes k_B T per mode.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions-residual-entropy> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''residual entropy''' ;
  skos:definition '''Non-zero entropy remaining at 0 K due to degeneracy in the ground state (e.g., CO, ice); S_0 = k_B ln(W).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions-symmetry-number-sigma> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''symmetry number (sigma)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The number of equivalent orientations of a molecule obtained by rotations; used to avoid overcounting in the rotational partition function.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions-zero-point-energy-zpe> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''zero-point energy (ZPE)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The energy (1/2)*h*nu_e of the lowest vibrational quantum level; non-zero even at absolute zero.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions-microcanonical-ensemble> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''microcanonical ensemble''' ;
  skos:definition '''An ensemble of isolated systems at fixed N, V, and E; entropy is S = k_B ln(Omega) where Omega is the number of microstates.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions-grand-canonical-ensemble> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''grand canonical ensemble''' ;
  skos:definition '''An ensemble at fixed mu (chemical potential), V, and T; useful for open systems where particle number fluctuates.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions-helmholtz-free-energy-from-q> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Helmholtz free energy from Q''' ;
  skos:definition '''A = -k_B T ln(Q); all other thermodynamic functions derived from A by standard relations.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions-molecular-partition-function> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Molecular partition function''' ;
  skos:definition '''q = sum_i g_i * exp(-E_i / (k_B*T))  where g_i is degeneracy of state i''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-chemistry-statistical-thermodynamics-and-partition-functions-canonical-partition-function-ideal-gas> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Canonical partition function (ideal gas)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Q = q^N / N!  (indistinguishable particles)''' ;
