<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals-peptide-bond> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''peptide bond''' ;
  skos:definition '''An amide bond formed between the alpha-carboxyl group of one amino acid and the alpha-amino group of another with loss of water; has partial double-bond character due to resonance.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals-isoelectric-point-pi> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''isoelectric point (pI)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The pH at which an amino acid (or protein) bears no net charge; pI = average of the pKa values flanking the zwitterion form.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals-michaelis-constant-k-m> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Michaelis constant (K_M)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The substrate concentration at which the reaction rate is half of V_max; reflects the affinity of the enzyme for its substrate (lower K_M = higher affinity).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals-competitive-inhibition> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''competitive inhibition''' ;
  skos:definition '''Inhibition in which the inhibitor competes with the substrate for the enzyme active site; increases apparent K_M, V_max unchanged.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals-allosteric-regulation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''allosteric regulation''' ;
  skos:definition '''Regulation of an enzyme by binding of a molecule (effector) at a site other than the active site, inducing a conformational change that alters activity.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals-atp-adenosine-triphosphate> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''ATP (adenosine triphosphate)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The primary energy currency of cells; hydrolysis of the terminal phosphoanhydride bond releases approximately -30.5 kJ/mol under standard biological conditions.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals-glycolysis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''glycolysis''' ;
  skos:definition '''The anaerobic metabolic pathway that converts one glucose (6C) to two pyruvate (3C) molecules, producing a net of 2 ATP and 2 NADH.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals-dna-double-helix> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''DNA double helix''' ;
  skos:definition '''The antiparallel, right-handed B-form double helix of DNA; adenine pairs with thymine (2 H-bonds), guanine pairs with cytosine (3 H-bonds).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals-phospholipid-bilayer> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''phospholipid bilayer''' ;
  skos:definition '''The fundamental structure of biological membranes; amphipathic phospholipids arrange with hydrophilic headgroups facing aqueous phases and hydrophobic tails forming the interior.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals-coenzyme> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''coenzyme''' ;
  skos:definition '''A non-protein organic molecule that assists an enzyme; examples include NAD+, FAD, coenzyme A, and ATP.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-chemistry-biochemistry-fundamentals> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
