<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> skos:scopeNote '''Limits and continuity; Differentiation rules and chain rule; Applications of derivatives (optimization, related rates); Mean value theorems; Integration: Riemann sums and antiderivatives; Techniques of integration; Improper integrals; Sequences and series: convergence tests, Taylor series''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-limit> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''limit''' ;
  skos:definition '''lim_{x→a} f(x) = L means for every ε > 0 there exists δ > 0 such that 0 < |x - a| < δ implies |f(x) - L| < ε.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-continuity> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''continuity''' ;
  skos:definition '''f is continuous at a if lim_{x→a} f(x) = f(a); continuous on an interval if continuous at each point.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-derivative> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''derivative''' ;
  skos:definition '''f'(x) = lim_{h→0} (f(x+h) - f(x))/h; the instantaneous rate of change of f at x.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-riemann-integral> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Riemann integral''' ;
  skos:definition '''∫_a^b f(x) dx = lim_{||P||→0} Σ f(x_i*) Δx_i; the limit of Riemann sums over partitions P of [a, b].''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-antiderivative> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''antiderivative''' ;
  skos:definition '''A function F such that F'(x) = f(x); also called an indefinite integral, written ∫ f(x) dx = F(x) + C.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-critical-point> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''critical point''' ;
  skos:definition '''A point c in the domain of f where f'(c) = 0 or f'(c) does not exist.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-inflection-point> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''inflection point''' ;
  skos:definition '''A point where f''changes sign (concavity changes from up to down or vice versa).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-taylor-series> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Taylor series''' ;
  skos:definition '''The power series Σ_{n=0}^∞ f^(n)(a)/n! · (x-a)^n representing f near x = a, when f is infinitely differentiable.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-radius-of-convergence> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''radius of convergence''' ;
  skos:definition '''For a power series Σ a_n x^n, the value R such that the series converges absolutely for |x| < R and diverges for |x| > R.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-fundamental-theorem-of-calculus-part-1> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Fundamental theorem of calculus (Part 1)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If F(x) = ∫_a^x f(t) dt, then F'(x) = f(x) wherever f is continuous.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-fundamental-theorem-of-calculus-part-2> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Fundamental theorem of calculus (Part 2)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''∫_a^b f(x) dx = F(b) - F(a) where F is any antiderivative of f.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-mean-value-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Mean value theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If f is continuous on [a,b] and differentiable on (a,b), then there exists c ∈ (a,b) with f'(c) = (f(b)-f(a))/(b-a).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-l-h-pital-s-rule> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''L'Hôpital's rule''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If lim f/g is 0/0 or ∞/∞, then lim f/g = lim f'/g' (provided the latter limit exists).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-chain-rule> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Chain rule''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''(f ∘ g)'(x) = f'(g(x)) · g'(x)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-product-rule> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Product rule''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''(fg)' = f'g + fg'''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-integration-by-parts> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Integration by parts''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''∫ u dv = uv - ∫ v du''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-ratio-test-for-series> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Ratio test for series''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If lim |a_{n+1}/a_n| = L < 1, the series Σ a_n converges absolutely; if L > 1, it diverges.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-taylor-s-theorem-with-remainder> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Taylor's theorem with remainder''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''f(x) = Σ_{k=0}^{n} f^(k)(a)/k! · (x-a)^k + R_n(x), where R_n(x) = f^(n+1)(c)/(n+1)! · (x-a)^(n+1) for some c between a and x.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-intermediate-value-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Intermediate value theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If f is continuous on [a,b] and f(a) < k < f(b), then there exists c ∈ (a,b) with f(c) = k.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-single-variable-calculus-standard-taylor-series> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Standard Taylor series''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''e^x = Σ x^n/n!; sin x = Σ (-1)^n x^(2n+1)/(2n+1)!; cos x = Σ (-1)^n x^(2n)/(2n)!; 1/(1-x) = Σ x^n for |x|<1''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-single-variable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Multivariable Calculus''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-mathematics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> skos:scopeNote '''Partial derivatives and gradients; Directional derivatives; Optimization: Lagrange multipliers; Multiple integrals (double and triple); Change of variables and Jacobians; Vector fields, divergence, and curl; Line integrals and surface integrals; Stokes', Green's, and Divergence theorems''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-partial-derivative> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''partial derivative''' ;
  skos:definition '''∂f/∂x is the derivative of f with respect to x holding all other variables fixed.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-gradient> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''gradient''' ;
  skos:definition '''∇f = (∂f/∂x, ∂f/∂y, ∂f/∂z); a vector pointing in the direction of steepest ascent of f.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-directional-derivative> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''directional derivative''' ;
  skos:definition '''D_u f(p) = ∇f(p) · u; the rate of change of f at p in the direction of unit vector u.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-jacobian> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Jacobian''' ;
  skos:definition '''The matrix of all first-order partial derivatives of a vector-valued function; its determinant measures the local change of area/volume under a coordinate transformation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-curl> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''curl''' ;
  skos:definition '''curl F = ∇ × F; measures the infinitesimal rotation of a vector field at each point.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-divergence> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''divergence''' ;
  skos:definition '''div F = ∇ · F = ∂F₁/∂x + ∂F₂/∂y + ∂F₃/∂z; measures the net outflow of a vector field per unit volume.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-conservative-vector-field> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''conservative vector field''' ;
  skos:definition '''A vector field F with curl F = 0 (equivalently, F = ∇f for some scalar potential f); line integrals are path-independent.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-saddle-point> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''saddle point''' ;
  skos:definition '''A critical point that is neither a local max nor a local min; the second derivative test gives a negative discriminant D = f_{xx}f_{yy} - f_{xy}².''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-clairaut-s-theorem-symmetry-of-mixed-partials> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Clairaut's theorem (symmetry of mixed partials)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If f_{xy} and f_{yx} are continuous near (a, b), then f_{xy}(a,b) = f_{yx}(a,b).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-second-derivative-test-two-variables> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Second derivative test (two variables)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Let D = f_{xx}f_{yy} - (f_{xy})² at critical point (a,b). If D > 0 and f_{xx} > 0: local min; f_{xx} < 0: local max; D < 0: saddle point.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-lagrange-multiplier-condition> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Lagrange multiplier condition''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''At a constrained extremum of f subject to g = 0: ∇f = λ∇g.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-change-of-variables-formula> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Change of variables formula''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''∫∫_R f(x,y) dA = ∫∫_S f(x(u,v), y(u,v)) |J(u,v)| du dv where J = ∂(x,y)/∂(u,v).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-green-s-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Green's theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''∮_C (P dx + Q dy) = ∬_D (∂Q/∂x - ∂P/∂y) dA (C positively oriented boundary of D).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-stokes-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Stokes' theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''∮_C F · dr = ∬_S (curl F) · dS where C = ∂S.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-divergence-theorem-gauss> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Divergence theorem (Gauss)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''∯_S F · dS = ∭_V (div F) dV where S = ∂V.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-multivariable-calculus-chain-rule-multivariable> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Chain rule (multivariable)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''dz/dt = (∂z/∂x)(dx/dt) + (∂z/∂y)(dy/dt)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-multivariable-calculus> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Linear Algebra''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-mathematics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> skos:scopeNote '''Vector spaces and subspaces; Linear independence, span, and basis; Linear transformations and matrix representations; Determinants; Eigenvalues and eigenvectors; Inner product spaces and orthogonality; Spectral theorem and diagonalization; Singular value decomposition''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-linear-algebra-vector-space> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''vector space''' ;
  skos:definition '''A set V with operations of addition and scalar multiplication satisfying 8 axioms (commutativity, associativity, distributivity, identities, inverses); elements are called vectors.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-linear-algebra-linear-independence> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''linear independence''' ;
  skos:definition '''Vectors v₁,...,v_n are linearly independent if c₁v₁ + ... + c_n v_n = 0 implies all c_i = 0.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-linear-algebra-basis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''basis''' ;
  skos:definition '''A linearly independent spanning set for a vector space; the number of elements is the dimension.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-linear-algebra-rank> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''rank''' ;
  skos:definition '''The dimension of the column space (or row space) of a matrix; equals the number of pivot columns in its row echelon form.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-linear-algebra-nullspace-kernel> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''nullspace (kernel)''' ;
  skos:definition '''ker(A) = {x : Ax = 0}; a subspace of the domain whose dimension is the nullity.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-linear-algebra-eigenvalue> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''eigenvalue''' ;
  skos:definition '''A scalar λ such that Av = λv for some nonzero vector v (the corresponding eigenvector).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-linear-algebra-characteristic-polynomial> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''characteristic polynomial''' ;
  skos:definition '''det(A - λI); its roots are the eigenvalues of A.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-linear-algebra-orthogonal-matrix> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''orthogonal matrix''' ;
  skos:definition '''A square matrix Q with Q^T Q = I; its columns form an orthonormal basis; det Q = ±1.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-linear-algebra-positive-definite-matrix> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''positive definite matrix''' ;
  skos:definition '''A symmetric matrix A such that x^T Ax > 0 for all nonzero x; equivalently, all eigenvalues are positive.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-linear-algebra-singular-matrix> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''singular matrix''' ;
  skos:definition '''A square matrix with determinant 0; equivalently, it has no inverse; equivalently, its columns are linearly dependent.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-linear-algebra-rank-nullity-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Rank-nullity theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''dim(ker T) + dim(im T) = dim(domain); rank(A) + nullity(A) = n for an m×n matrix.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-linear-algebra-spectral-theorem-real-symmetric-matrices> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Spectral theorem (real symmetric matrices)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every real symmetric matrix A is orthogonally diagonalizable: A = Q Λ Q^T where Q is orthogonal and Λ is diagonal with real eigenvalues.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-linear-algebra-cayley-hamilton-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Cayley-Hamilton theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every square matrix satisfies its own characteristic polynomial: p(A) = 0.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-linear-algebra-determinant-expansion-and-properties> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Determinant expansion and properties''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''det(AB) = det(A)det(B); det(A^T) = det(A); det(A⁻¹) = 1/det(A); row-swap negates det.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-linear-algebra-gram-schmidt-process> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Gram-Schmidt process''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Given basis {v_i}, define orthonormal basis {e_i} by e_k = (v_k - Σ_{j<k} (v_k · e_j)e_j) / ‖...‖.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-linear-algebra-diagonalization-criterion> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Diagonalization criterion''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''An n×n matrix A is diagonalizable iff it has n linearly independent eigenvectors; equivalently, the geometric multiplicity equals algebraic multiplicity for every eigenvalue.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-linear-algebra-singular-value-decomposition> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Singular value decomposition''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Any m×n matrix A = UΣV^T where U (m×m), V (n×n) are orthogonal and Σ is m×n diagonal with singular values σ_i ≥ 0.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-linear-algebra-invertibility-equivalences> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Invertibility equivalences''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''TFAE: A is invertible, det A ≠ 0, rank A = n, Ax=0 has only trivial solution, Ax=b has unique solution for every b.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-linear-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Differential Equations''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-mathematics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> skos:scopeNote '''First-order ODEs: separable, linear, exact; Second-order linear ODEs with constant coefficients; Method of undetermined coefficients and variation of parameters; Laplace transforms; Systems of ODEs and phase plane analysis; Power series solutions and Frobenius method; Partial differential equations: heat, wave, Laplace equations''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-differential-equations-ordinary-differential-equation-ode> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''ordinary differential equation (ODE)''' ;
  skos:definition '''An equation relating a function y(x) and its derivatives; order is the highest derivative present.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-differential-equations-separable-ode> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''separable ODE''' ;
  skos:definition '''An ODE of the form dy/dx = f(x)g(y), solvable by separating variables: ∫ dy/g(y) = ∫ f(x) dx.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-differential-equations-integrating-factor> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''integrating factor''' ;
  skos:definition '''A function μ(x) multiplied through a linear ODE dy/dx + P(x)y = Q(x) to make the left side an exact derivative; μ(x) = e^(∫P dx).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-differential-equations-characteristic-equation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''characteristic equation''' ;
  skos:definition '''For ay'' + by' + cy = 0, the algebraic equation ar² + br + c = 0 whose roots determine the general solution.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-differential-equations-wronskian> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Wronskian''' ;
  skos:definition '''W(y₁, y₂) = y₁y₂' - y₁'y₂; if W ≠ 0 on an interval, y₁ and y₂ are linearly independent solutions.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-differential-equations-laplace-transform> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Laplace transform''' ;
  skos:definition '''L{f(t)} = F(s) = ∫_0^∞ e^(-st) f(t) dt; transforms a differential equation into an algebraic equation in s.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-differential-equations-equilibrium-solution> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''equilibrium solution''' ;
  skos:definition '''A constant solution y = c where f(c) = 0; stable if nearby solutions approach it, unstable if they diverge.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-differential-equations-eigenfunction-expansion> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''eigenfunction expansion''' ;
  skos:definition '''Representation of a function as a series of eigenfunctions of a differential operator (e.g., Fourier series in terms of sin and cos).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-differential-equations-general-solution-of-2nd-order-linear-ode-constant-coefficients> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''General solution of 2nd-order linear ODE (constant coefficients)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Roots r₁ ≠ r₂ real: y = c₁e^(r₁x) + c₂e^(r₂x); repeated root r: y = (c₁ + c₂x)e^(rx); complex roots α ± βi: y = e^(αx)(c₁cos βx + c₂sin βx).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-differential-equations-variation-of-parameters-formula> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Variation of parameters formula''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''y_p = y₁ ∫(-y₂ g/W) dx + y₂ ∫(y₁ g/W) dx where W = Wronskian(y₁, y₂).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-differential-equations-existence-and-uniqueness-theorem-picard-lindel-f> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Existence and uniqueness theorem (Picard-Lindelöf)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If f(x,y) and ∂f/∂y are continuous in a rectangle containing (x₀, y₀), then the IVP y' = f(x,y), y(x₀)=y₀ has a unique solution.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-differential-equations-laplace-transform-of-derivative> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Laplace transform of derivative''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''L{y'} = sY(s) - y(0); L{y''} = s²Y(s) - sy(0) - y'(0)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-differential-equations-convolution-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Convolution theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''L{(f * g)(t)} = F(s)G(s); L⁻¹{F(s)G(s)} = ∫_0^t f(τ)g(t-τ) dτ''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-differential-equations-heat-equation> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Heat equation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''u_t = α² u_{xx}; solved on [0,L] by separation of variables giving u(x,t) = Σ B_n sin(nπx/L) e^(-α²(nπ/L)²t)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-differential-equations-wave-equation> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Wave equation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''u_{tt} = c² u_{xx}; D'Alembert solution: u(x,t) = (1/2)[f(x+ct)+f(x-ct)] + (1/2c)∫_{x-ct}^{x+ct} g(s) ds''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-differential-equations> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Probability and Combinatorics''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-mathematics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> skos:scopeNote '''Counting: permutations, combinations, pigeonhole principle; Probability axioms and conditional probability; Bayes' theorem and independence; Discrete distributions: Bernoulli, Binomial, Poisson, Geometric; Continuous distributions: Uniform, Normal, Exponential; Expectation, variance, and moments; Law of large numbers and central limit theorem; Markov chains''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-sample-space> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''sample space''' ;
  skos:definition '''The set Ω of all possible outcomes of a random experiment.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-event> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''event''' ;
  skos:definition '''A subset of the sample space; a measurable collection of outcomes to which a probability is assigned.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-conditional-probability> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''conditional probability''' ;
  skos:definition '''P(A|B) = P(A ∩ B)/P(B) for P(B) > 0; the probability of A given that B has occurred.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-independence> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''independence''' ;
  skos:definition '''Events A and B are independent if P(A ∩ B) = P(A)P(B); knowing B gives no information about A.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-random-variable> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''random variable''' ;
  skos:definition '''A measurable function X: Ω → ℝ that assigns a numerical value to each outcome.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-expected-value> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''expected value''' ;
  skos:definition '''E[X] = Σ x P(X=x) (discrete) or ∫ x f(x) dx (continuous); the probability-weighted average value.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-variance> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''variance''' ;
  skos:definition '''Var(X) = E[(X - μ)²] = E[X²] - (E[X])²; measures spread around the mean.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-moment-generating-function> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''moment generating function''' ;
  skos:definition '''M_X(t) = E[e^{tX}]; its k-th derivative at t=0 equals the k-th moment E[X^k].''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-cumulative-distribution-function> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''cumulative distribution function''' ;
  skos:definition '''F(x) = P(X ≤ x); a right-continuous, non-decreasing function from ℝ to [0,1].''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-bayes-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Bayes' theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''P(A|B) = P(B|A)P(A)/P(B) = P(B|A)P(A) / [P(B|A)P(A) + P(B|Aᶜ)P(Aᶜ)]''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-law-of-total-probability> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Law of total probability''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''P(B) = Σ_i P(B|A_i)P(A_i) for any partition {A_i} of Ω.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-binomial-distribution> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Binomial distribution''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''P(X=k) = C(n,k) p^k (1-p)^(n-k); E[X]=np; Var(X)=np(1-p)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-poisson-distribution> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Poisson distribution''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''P(X=k) = e^(-λ)λ^k/k!; E[X]=Var(X)=λ; arises as limit of Binomial as n→∞, p→0, np→λ.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-normal-distribution> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Normal distribution''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''f(x) = (1/σ√(2π)) exp(-(x-μ)²/(2σ²)); E[X]=μ, Var(X)=σ²''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-central-limit-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Central limit theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If X₁,...,X_n are i.i.d. with mean μ and variance σ², then (X̄_n - μ)/(σ/√n) → N(0,1) in distribution as n → ∞.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-law-of-large-numbers-strong> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Law of large numbers (strong)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If X₁, X₂,... are i.i.d. with E[X₁] = μ, then X̄_n = (X₁+...+X_n)/n → μ almost surely.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-pigeonhole-principle> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Pigeonhole principle''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If n+1 objects are placed into n boxes, then at least one box contains two or more objects.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics-inclusion-exclusion-principle> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Inclusion-exclusion principle''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''|A₁ ∪ ... ∪ A_n| = Σ|A_i| - Σ|A_i ∩ A_j| + Σ|A_i ∩ A_j ∩ A_k| - ... ± |A₁∩...∩A_n|''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-probability-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Statistics''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-mathematics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> skos:scopeNote '''Descriptive statistics: mean, median, variance, IQR; Sampling distributions and the standard error; Confidence intervals; Hypothesis testing: z-test, t-test, chi-square; p-values and significance; Regression and correlation; ANOVA; Nonparametric tests''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-statistics-population-vs-sample> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''population vs. sample''' ;
  skos:definition '''A population is the entire set of subjects; a sample is a subset drawn from it. Statistics from samples estimate population parameters.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-statistics-standard-error> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''standard error''' ;
  skos:definition '''The standard deviation of the sampling distribution of a statistic; for the sample mean, SE = σ/√n.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-statistics-confidence-interval> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''confidence interval''' ;
  skos:definition '''An interval [L, U] constructed from data such that it contains the true parameter with a stated probability (confidence level) in repeated sampling.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-statistics-null-hypothesis-h> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''null hypothesis (H₀)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The default claim being tested; typically a statement of no effect or no difference.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-statistics-p-value> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''p-value''' ;
  skos:definition '''The probability of obtaining a test statistic at least as extreme as observed, assuming H₀ is true; small p-values provide evidence against H₀.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-statistics-type-i-error> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Type I error (α)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Rejecting H₀ when it is true; probability is the significance level α.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-statistics-type-ii-error> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Type II error (β)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Failing to reject H₀ when it is false; power = 1 - β.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-statistics-correlation-coefficient-r> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''correlation coefficient (r)''' ;
  skos:definition '''r = Cov(X,Y)/(σ_X σ_Y); ranges from -1 to 1; measures the linear association between two variables.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-statistics-regression-coefficient> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''regression coefficient''' ;
  skos:definition '''In ŷ = a + bx, the slope b = r · (s_y/s_x) = Σ(x_i - x̄)(y_i - ȳ) / Σ(x_i - x̄)².''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-statistics-z-test-statistic> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Z-test statistic''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''z = (X̄ - μ₀) / (σ/√n); used when population σ is known.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-statistics-t-test-statistic-one-sample> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''t-test statistic (one sample)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''t = (X̄ - μ₀) / (s/√n); follows t-distribution with n-1 degrees of freedom.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-statistics-chi-square-goodness-of-fit-statistic> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Chi-square goodness-of-fit statistic''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''χ² = Σ (O_i - E_i)² / E_i; follows χ²(k-1) distribution under H₀.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-statistics-least-squares-regression-line> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Least-squares regression line''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''ŷ = ȳ + r(s_y/s_x)(x - x̄); minimizes Σ(y_i - ŷ_i)².''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-statistics-95-confidence-interval-for-mean> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''95% confidence interval for mean''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''X̄ ± t*(s/√n) where t* is the critical value for t_{n-1} at 95%.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-statistics-chebyshev-s-inequality> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Chebyshev's inequality''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''P(|X - μ| ≥ kσ) ≤ 1/k² for any k > 0; distribution-free bound.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-statistics-neyman-pearson-lemma> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Neyman-Pearson lemma''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''The most powerful test at level α for H₀: θ=θ₀ vs H₁: θ=θ₁ rejects based on the likelihood ratio L(θ₁)/L(θ₀) > c.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-statistics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Abstract Algebra — Group Theory''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-mathematics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> skos:scopeNote '''Groups: definition, examples (Z, Z_n, S_n, D_n, GL_n); Subgroups and cosets; Normal subgroups and quotient groups; Group homomorphisms and isomorphisms; Cyclic groups and generators; Permutation groups and Cayley's theorem; Group actions, orbits, and stabilizers; Sylow theorems''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-group> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''group''' ;
  skos:definition '''A set G with a binary operation · satisfying: (i) closure, (ii) associativity, (iii) existence of identity e with ge = eg = g, (iv) existence of inverses g⁻¹ with gg⁻¹ = e.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-abelian-group> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''abelian group''' ;
  skos:definition '''A group in which the operation is commutative: ab = ba for all a, b.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-order-of-a-group> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''order of a group''' ;
  skos:definition '''|G|, the cardinality of the set G.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-order-of-an-element> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''order of an element''' ;
  skos:definition '''The smallest positive integer n such that g^n = e; if no such n exists, the element has infinite order.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-subgroup> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''subgroup''' ;
  skos:definition '''A subset H ⊆ G closed under the group operation and inverses, forming a group in its own right. Equivalently: H ≠ ∅ and a,b ∈ H ⟹ ab⁻¹ ∈ H.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-normal-subgroup> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''normal subgroup''' ;
  skos:definition '''A subgroup N ⊴ G such that gNg⁻¹ = N for all g ∈ G; equivalently, left and right cosets coincide.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-coset> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''coset''' ;
  skos:definition '''A left coset of H in G is gH = {gh : h ∈ H}; the cosets partition G into equal-sized subsets.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-quotient-group> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''quotient group''' ;
  skos:definition '''G/N where N ⊴ G; the set of cosets {gN} with multiplication (aN)(bN) = (ab)N.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-group-homomorphism> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''group homomorphism''' ;
  skos:definition '''A function φ: G → H satisfying φ(ab) = φ(a)φ(b) for all a, b ∈ G.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-kernel> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''kernel''' ;
  skos:definition '''ker φ = {g ∈ G : φ(g) = e_H}; always a normal subgroup of G.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-simple-group> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''simple group''' ;
  skos:definition '''A nontrivial group with no proper nontrivial normal subgroups.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-p-group> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''p-group''' ;
  skos:definition '''A group whose order is a power of a prime p; every nontrivial p-group has a nontrivial center.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-lagrange-s-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Lagrange's theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If H is a subgroup of a finite group G, then |H| divides |G|, and the index [G:H] = |G|/|H| equals the number of distinct cosets of H.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-corollary-order-of-elements-divides-group-order> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Corollary: order of elements divides group order''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''The order of any element g ∈ G divides |G|; in particular, g^|G| = e.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-first-isomorphism-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''First isomorphism theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If φ: G → H is a group homomorphism, then G/ker φ ≅ im φ.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-second-isomorphism-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Second isomorphism theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If H ≤ G and N ⊴ G, then H/(H ∩ N) ≅ HN/N.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-third-isomorphism-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Third isomorphism theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If N ⊴ K ⊴ G and N ⊴ G, then (G/N)/(K/N) ≅ G/K.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-cayley-s-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Cayley's theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every group G is isomorphic to a subgroup of the symmetric group S_{|G|}; each g ∈ G acts by left multiplication.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-sylow-s-first-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Sylow's first theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If p^k divides |G|, then G has a subgroup of order p^k.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-sylow-s-second-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Sylow's second theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Any two Sylow p-subgroups of G are conjugate.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-sylow-s-third-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Sylow's third theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''The number n_p of Sylow p-subgroups satisfies n_p ≡ 1 (mod p) and n_p divides |G|/p^k.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-orbit-stabilizer-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Orbit-stabilizer theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''|G| = |Orb(x)| · |Stab(x)| for any group action of G on a set X and any x ∈ X.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-classification-of-finite-cyclic-groups> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Classification of finite cyclic groups''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every cyclic group of order n is isomorphic to Z_n; every subgroup of Z_n is cyclic of order dividing n.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory-cauchy-s-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Cauchy's theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If prime p divides |G|, then G has an element of order p.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-group-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Abstract Algebra — Rings and Fields''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-mathematics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> skos:scopeNote '''Rings: definition, subrings, ring homomorphisms; Ideals and quotient rings; Integral domains and fields; Principal ideal domains (PIDs) and UFDs; Polynomial rings; Field extensions and algebraic elements; Splitting fields and algebraic closure; Galois theory (introduction)''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-ring> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''ring''' ;
  skos:definition '''A set R with addition and multiplication satisfying: (R,+) is an abelian group, multiplication is associative, and distributive laws hold.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-commutative-ring> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''commutative ring''' ;
  skos:definition '''A ring in which multiplication is commutative: ab = ba for all a, b.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-unity-multiplicative-identity> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''unity (multiplicative identity)''' ;
  skos:definition '''An element 1 ∈ R such that 1·a = a·1 = a for all a; a ring with unity is called a unital ring.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-ideal> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''ideal''' ;
  skos:definition '''A subset I ⊆ R closed under addition and satisfying rI ⊆ I and Ir ⊆ I for all r ∈ R; the kernel of any ring homomorphism is an ideal.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-prime-ideal> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''prime ideal''' ;
  skos:definition '''An ideal P ≠ R such that ab ∈ P implies a ∈ P or b ∈ P; R/P is an integral domain iff P is prime.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-maximal-ideal> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''maximal ideal''' ;
  skos:definition '''An ideal M ≠ R with no ideal strictly between M and R; R/M is a field iff M is maximal.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-integral-domain> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''integral domain''' ;
  skos:definition '''A commutative unital ring with no zero divisors; ab = 0 implies a = 0 or b = 0.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-field> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''field''' ;
  skos:definition '''A commutative ring in which every nonzero element has a multiplicative inverse; equivalently, a commutative division ring.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-ufd-unique-factorization-domain> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''UFD (unique factorization domain)''' ;
  skos:definition '''An integral domain in which every nonzero non-unit element factors uniquely into irreducibles (up to order and units).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-pid-principal-ideal-domain> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''PID (principal ideal domain)''' ;
  skos:definition '''An integral domain in which every ideal is principal, i.e., generated by a single element.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-algebraic-element> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''algebraic element''' ;
  skos:definition '''An element α over a field F is algebraic if it satisfies some nonzero polynomial with coefficients in F; otherwise it is transcendental.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-degree-of-field-extension> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''degree of field extension''' ;
  skos:definition '''[E:F] = dim_F E; the dimension of E as a vector space over F.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-first-isomorphism-theorem-for-rings> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''First isomorphism theorem for rings''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If φ: R → S is a ring homomorphism, then R/ker φ ≅ im φ.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-correspondence-theorem-rings> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Correspondence theorem (rings)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''There is a bijection between ideals of R containing I and ideals of R/I, preserving inclusion, primality, and maximality.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-every-pid-is-a-ufd> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Every PID is a UFD''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''In a PID, every nonzero non-unit element factors uniquely into irreducibles; every irreducible is prime.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-gauss-s-lemma> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Gauss's lemma''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''The product of primitive polynomials in Z[x] is primitive; consequently Z[x] is a UFD.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-eisenstein-s-irreducibility-criterion> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Eisenstein's irreducibility criterion''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If f = a_n x^n + ... + a_0 ∈ Z[x] and prime p divides a_0,...,a_{n-1} but not a_n, and p² does not divide a_0, then f is irreducible over Q.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-tower-law-for-field-extensions> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Tower law for field extensions''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''[E:F] = [E:K][K:F] for fields F ⊆ K ⊆ E.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-characterization-of-simple-extensions> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Characterization of simple extensions''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''F(α) ≅ F[x]/(m_α(x)) where m_α is the minimal polynomial of α; [F(α):F] = deg m_α.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-fundamental-theorem-of-galois-theory> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Fundamental theorem of Galois theory''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''For a Galois extension E/F with group G = Gal(E/F): there is an inclusion-reversing bijection between subgroups of G and intermediate fields K (F ⊆ K ⊆ E); [G:H] = [K_H:F] and |H| = [E:K_H].''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields-algebraic-closure-existence> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Algebraic closure existence''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every field F has an algebraic closure F̄ (algebraically closed and algebraic over F); it is unique up to isomorphism over F.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-abstract-algebra-rings-and-fields> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Real Analysis''' ;
  kcc:level '''graduate''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-mathematics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> skos:scopeNote '''Construction of real numbers; completeness; Metric spaces: open, closed, compact, connected sets; Sequences and series of functions: uniform convergence; Continuity, uniform continuity, Lipschitz conditions; Differentiation: mean value theorem, Taylor's theorem; Riemann and Lebesgue integration; Measure theory: σ-algebras, measures, measurable functions; L^p spaces and Hilbert spaces''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-real-analysis-completeness> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''completeness''' ;
  skos:definition '''A metric space is complete if every Cauchy sequence converges; the reals are the unique (up to isomorphism) complete ordered field.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-real-analysis-open-set> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''open set''' ;
  skos:definition '''A set U in a metric space such that every point has an open ball entirely within U; equivalently, U = int(U).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-real-analysis-compact-set> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''compact set''' ;
  skos:definition '''A set K where every open cover has a finite subcover; in ℝⁿ, equivalently, closed and bounded (Heine-Borel).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-real-analysis-uniform-continuity> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''uniform continuity''' ;
  skos:definition '''f is uniformly continuous on E if for all ε > 0 there exists δ > 0 such that d(x,y) < δ implies |f(x)-f(y)| < ε, with δ independent of the choice of x.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-real-analysis-uniform-convergence> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''uniform convergence''' ;
  skos:definition '''f_n → f uniformly on E if sup_{x∈E} |f_n(x) - f(x)| → 0; it preserves continuity, and allows interchange of limit and integral.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-real-analysis-algebra> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''σ-algebra''' ;
  skos:definition '''A collection Σ of subsets of a set X closed under complements and countable unions; provides the domain for a measure.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-real-analysis-measure> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''measure''' ;
  skos:definition '''A countably additive function μ: Σ → [0,∞] on a σ-algebra with μ(∅) = 0.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-real-analysis-lebesgue-measurable> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Lebesgue measurable''' ;
  skos:definition '''A set E ⊆ ℝ is Lebesgue measurable if for all ε > 0 there is an open set U ⊇ E with m(U\\ E) < ε (outer-regularity characterization).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-real-analysis-almost-everywhere-a-e> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''almost everywhere (a.e.)''' ;
  skos:definition '''A property holds almost everywhere if the set of points where it fails has measure zero.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-real-analysis-l-p-space> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''L^p space''' ;
  skos:definition '''L^p(μ) = {f measurable : ∫|f|^p dμ < ∞} with norm ‖f‖_p = (∫|f|^p dμ)^(1/p); a Banach space for 1 ≤ p ≤ ∞.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-real-analysis-completeness-of-least-upper-bound-property> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Completeness of ℝ (least upper bound property)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every nonempty subset of ℝ that is bounded above has a supremum in ℝ.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-real-analysis-bolzano-weierstrass-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Bolzano-Weierstrass theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every bounded sequence in ℝⁿ has a convergent subsequence.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-real-analysis-heine-borel-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Heine-Borel theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''A subset of ℝⁿ is compact if and only if it is closed and bounded.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-real-analysis-intermediate-value-theorem-analysis-form> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Intermediate value theorem (analysis form)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If f: [a,b] → ℝ is continuous and f(a) < 0 < f(b), then there exists c ∈ (a,b) with f(c) = 0.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-real-analysis-uniform-limit-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Uniform limit theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If f_n → f uniformly on E and each f_n is continuous, then f is continuous.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-real-analysis-weierstrass-m-test> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Weierstrass M-test''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If |f_n(x)| ≤ M_n for all x and Σ M_n < ∞, then Σ f_n converges uniformly and absolutely.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-real-analysis-lebesgue-dominated-convergence-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Lebesgue dominated convergence theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If f_n → f a.e. and |f_n| ≤ g with g integrable, then ∫ f_n → ∫ f.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-real-analysis-monotone-convergence-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Monotone convergence theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If 0 ≤ f_n ↑ f a.e., then ∫ f_n → ∫ f (possibly ∞).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-real-analysis-fatou-s-lemma> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Fatou's lemma''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''For nonneg. measurable f_n: ∫ liminf f_n ≤ liminf ∫ f_n.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-real-analysis-h-lder-s-inequality> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Hölder's inequality''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''∫|fg| dμ ≤ ‖f‖_p ‖g‖_q for 1/p + 1/q = 1 (conjugate exponents).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-real-analysis-fubini-s-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Fubini's theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''For integrable f on a product measure space: ∫∫ f(x,y) d(μ×ν) = ∫(∫ f(x,y) dν) dμ = ∫(∫ f(x,y) dμ) dν.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-real-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Complex Analysis''' ;
  kcc:level '''graduate''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-mathematics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> skos:scopeNote '''Complex differentiability and holomorphic functions; Cauchy-Riemann equations; Complex integration and Cauchy's theorem; Power series and analytic functions; Singularities: removable, poles, essential; Laurent series and residues; Conformal mappings and Möbius transformations; Entire and meromorphic functions''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-complex-analysis-holomorphic-function> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''holomorphic function''' ;
  skos:definition '''A function f: U → ℂ (U open in ℂ) that is complex-differentiable at every point of U; equivalently, satisfies the Cauchy-Riemann equations with continuous partials.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-complex-analysis-analytic-function> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''analytic function''' ;
  skos:definition '''A function representable by a convergent power series in a neighborhood of each point; for complex functions, analyticity and holomorphicity are equivalent.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-complex-analysis-cauchy-riemann-equations> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Cauchy-Riemann equations''' ;
  skos:definition '''For f = u + iv: ∂u/∂x = ∂v/∂y and ∂u/∂y = -∂v/∂x; necessary and (with continuous partials) sufficient for holomorphicity.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-complex-analysis-contour-integral> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''contour integral''' ;
  skos:definition '''∫_γ f(z) dz = ∫_a^b f(γ(t))γ'(t) dt for a parameterized curve γ: [a,b] → ℂ.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-complex-analysis-isolated-singularity> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''isolated singularity''' ;
  skos:definition '''A point z₀ where f is not defined or not holomorphic, but f is holomorphic in some punctured disk 0 < |z - z₀| < r.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-complex-analysis-residue> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''residue''' ;
  skos:definition '''Res(f, z₀) = a₋₁, the coefficient of (z - z₀)⁻¹ in the Laurent expansion of f at z₀; for a simple pole: Res(f, z₀) = lim_{z→z₀} (z-z₀)f(z).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-complex-analysis-m-bius-transformation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Möbius transformation''' ;
  skos:definition '''A map z ↦ (az+b)/(cz+d) with ad - bc ≠ 0; a bijection of the Riemann sphere ℂ∪{∞} that maps circles and lines to circles and lines.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-complex-analysis-entire-function> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''entire function''' ;
  skos:definition '''A function holomorphic on all of ℂ (no singularities in the finite plane); e.g., e^z, sin z, polynomials.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-complex-analysis-meromorphic-function> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''meromorphic function''' ;
  skos:definition '''A function holomorphic on a domain except at isolated poles; locally a ratio of holomorphic functions.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-complex-analysis-cauchy-s-integral-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Cauchy's integral theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If f is holomorphic on a simply connected domain D and γ is a closed contour in D, then ∮_γ f(z) dz = 0.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-complex-analysis-cauchy-s-integral-formula> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Cauchy's integral formula''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''f^(n)(z₀) = (n!)/(2πi) ∮_γ f(z)/(z - z₀)^(n+1) dz for n = 0, 1, 2,...''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-complex-analysis-residue-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Residue theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''∮_γ f(z) dz = 2πi Σ_k Res(f, z_k) where the sum is over poles z_k enclosed by γ (counted with winding number).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-complex-analysis-liouville-s-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Liouville's theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every bounded entire function is constant.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-complex-analysis-fundamental-theorem-of-algebra-complex-analysis-proof> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Fundamental theorem of algebra (complex analysis proof)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every non-constant polynomial has a root in ℂ (follows from Liouville: if p(z) ≠ 0 everywhere, then 1/p is bounded entire, hence constant).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-complex-analysis-identity-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Identity theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If f and g are holomorphic on a connected domain D and f = g on a set with an accumulation point in D, then f = g on all of D.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-complex-analysis-maximum-modulus-principle> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Maximum modulus principle''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''A nonconstant holomorphic function on a domain D cannot attain its maximum modulus on the interior of D.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-complex-analysis-riemann-mapping-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Riemann mapping theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Any simply connected proper open subset of ℂ is conformally equivalent to the open unit disk.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-complex-analysis-laurent-series> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Laurent series''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''On an annulus r < |z - z₀| < R: f(z) = Σ_{n=-∞}^{∞} a_n (z - z₀)^n where a_n = (1/2πi) ∮ f(z)/(z-z₀)^(n+1) dz.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-complex-analysis-argument-principle> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Argument principle''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''(1/2πi) ∮_γ f'(z)/f(z) dz = Z - P, where Z = number of zeros and P = number of poles of f inside γ (counted with multiplicity).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-complex-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Number Theory''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-mathematics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> skos:scopeNote '''Divisibility and prime factorization; Congruences and modular arithmetic; Euler's and Fermat's theorems; Chinese remainder theorem; Quadratic residues and Legendre symbol; Arithmetic functions: φ, τ, σ, μ; Continued fractions; Gaussian integers and algebraic integers''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-number-theory-congruence> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''congruence''' ;
  skos:definition '''a ≡ b (mod n) means n divides (a - b); this is an equivalence relation on ℤ compatible with + and ×.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-number-theory-euler-s-totient-function-n> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Euler's totient function φ(n)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The count of integers in {1,...,n} coprime to n; φ(n) = n ∏_{p|n} (1 - 1/p).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-number-theory-primitive-root-mod-n> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''primitive root (mod n)''' ;
  skos:definition '''An integer g whose powers g¹, g², ..., g^{φ(n)} generate all units mod n; exists iff n = 1, 2, 4, p^k, or 2p^k for odd prime p.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-number-theory-quadratic-residue> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''quadratic residue''' ;
  skos:definition '''An integer a coprime to p is a quadratic residue mod p if a ≡ x² (mod p) has a solution; otherwise a nonresidue.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-number-theory-legendre-symbol> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Legendre symbol''' ;
  skos:definition '''(a/p) = 1 if a is a QR mod p, -1 if nonresidue, 0 if p|a; computable via Euler's criterion (a/p) ≡ a^((p-1)/2) (mod p).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-number-theory-arithmetic-function> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''arithmetic function''' ;
  skos:definition '''A function f: ℕ → ℂ; it is multiplicative if gcd(m,n)=1 implies f(mn)=f(m)f(n).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-number-theory-m-bius-function-n> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Möbius function μ(n)''' ;
  skos:definition '''μ(1)=1; μ(n)=(-1)^k if n is a product of k distinct primes; μ(n)=0 if n has a squared prime factor.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-number-theory-gaussian-integer> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Gaussian integer''' ;
  skos:definition '''A complex number a + bi with a, b ∈ ℤ; forms a UFD Z[i] in which the Euclidean algorithm applies with norm N(a+bi) = a²+b².''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-number-theory-fermat-s-little-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Fermat's little theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If p is prime and p ∤ a, then a^(p-1) ≡ 1 (mod p); equivalently a^p ≡ a (mod p) for all a.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-number-theory-euler-s-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Euler's theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If gcd(a,n) = 1, then a^{φ(n)} ≡ 1 (mod n); generalizes Fermat's little theorem.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-number-theory-chinese-remainder-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Chinese remainder theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If n₁,...,n_k are pairwise coprime, the system x ≡ a_i (mod n_i) has a unique solution mod n₁...n_k.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-number-theory-wilson-s-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Wilson's theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''(p-1)! ≡ -1 (mod p) if and only if p is prime.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-number-theory-quadratic-reciprocity> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Quadratic reciprocity''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''For distinct odd primes p, q: (p/q)(q/p) = (-1)^{(p-1)(q-1)/4}; with supplements (−1/p) = (-1)^{(p-1)/2} and (2/p) = (-1)^{(p²-1)/8}.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-number-theory-m-bius-inversion-formula> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Möbius inversion formula''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If f(n) = Σ_{d|n} g(d), then g(n) = Σ_{d|n} μ(n/d) f(d).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-number-theory-sum-of-two-squares-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Sum of two squares theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''A positive integer n is a sum of two squares iff in the prime factorization of n, every prime p ≡ 3 (mod 4) occurs to an even power.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-number-theory-dirichlet-s-theorem-on-primes-in-arithmetic-progressions> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Dirichlet's theorem on primes in arithmetic progressions''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If gcd(a, m) = 1, then the arithmetic progression a, a+m, a+2m,... contains infinitely many primes.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-number-theory-euclidean-algorithm-for-gcd> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Euclidean algorithm for gcd''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''gcd(a,b) = gcd(b, a mod b); terminates and expresses gcd as integer linear combination (Bezout's identity: gcd(a,b) = sa+tb).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-number-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Discrete Mathematics and Combinatorics''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
