<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> skos:scopeNote '''Sets, relations, and functions; Mathematical induction and recursion; Counting: permutations, combinations, multinomials; Graph theory: paths, trees, coloring; Generating functions; Recurrence relations; Boolean algebra and logic; Ramsey theory (intro)''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-partial-order> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''partial order''' ;
  skos:definition '''A relation ≤ on a set that is reflexive (a≤a), antisymmetric (a≤b and b≤a implies a=b), and transitive (a≤b and b≤c implies a≤c).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-equivalence-relation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''equivalence relation''' ;
  skos:definition '''A relation that is reflexive, symmetric, and transitive; partitions the set into equivalence classes.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-graph> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''graph''' ;
  skos:definition '''A pair G = (V, E) of a vertex set V and an edge set E ⊆ V×V; may be directed or undirected, simple or multi.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-tree> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''tree''' ;
  skos:definition '''A connected acyclic graph; a tree on n vertices has exactly n-1 edges.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-planar-graph> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''planar graph''' ;
  skos:definition '''A graph that can be drawn in the plane without edge crossings.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-chromatic-number-g> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''chromatic number χ(G)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The minimum number of colors needed to color the vertices of G so that no two adjacent vertices share a color.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-generating-function> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''generating function''' ;
  skos:definition '''A formal power series f(x) = Σ a_n x^n encoding the sequence (a_n); used to solve recurrences and count combinatorial structures.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-derangement> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''derangement''' ;
  skos:definition '''A permutation with no fixed points; the number of derangements D_n = n! Σ_{k=0}^{n} (-1)^k/k! ≈ n!/e.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-catalan-number> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Catalan number''' ;
  skos:definition '''C_n = (1/(n+1))C(2n,n); counts many combinatorial structures including valid parenthesizations, binary trees, and Dyck paths.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-principle-of-mathematical-induction> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Principle of mathematical induction''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If P(1) is true and P(k) implies P(k+1) for all k ≥ 1, then P(n) is true for all positive integers n.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-strong-induction> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Strong induction''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If [P(1) ∧ ... ∧ P(k) ⟹ P(k+1)] for all k, then P(n) holds for all n.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-inclusion-exclusion-combinatorial> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Inclusion-exclusion (combinatorial)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''|A₁ ∪...∪ A_n| = Σ|A_i| - Σ|A_i∩A_j| + ... ± |A₁∩...∩A_n|''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-stars-and-bars-integer-compositions> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Stars and bars (integer compositions)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''The number of ways to write n as an ordered sum of k non-negative integers is C(n+k-1, k-1).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-euler-s-formula-for-planar-graphs> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Euler's formula for planar graphs''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''V - E + F = 2 for any connected planar graph with V vertices, E edges, and F faces (including outer face).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-four-color-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Four color theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every planar graph is 4-colorable (every planar map can be colored with 4 colors so no adjacent regions share a color).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-handshaking-lemma> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Handshaking lemma''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''In any graph, Σ deg(v) = 2|E|; in particular, the number of odd-degree vertices is even.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-burnside-s-lemma-polya-enumeration> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Burnside's lemma (Polya enumeration)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''The number of distinct orbits under a group G acting on set X is (1/|G|) Σ_{g∈G} |X^g| where X^g = {x : gx = x}.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics-ramsey-s-theorem-finite> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Ramsey's theorem (finite)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''For any r, s there exists R(r,s) such that any 2-coloring of edges of K_{R(r,s)} contains a red K_r or blue K_s.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-discrete-mathematics-and-combinatorics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Topology''' ;
  kcc:level '''graduate''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-mathematics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> skos:scopeNote '''Topological spaces: open sets, basis, subbasis; Continuity, homeomorphisms, and topological invariants; Connectedness and path-connectedness; Compactness: Tychonoff's theorem; Separation axioms (T₀ through T₄); Homotopy and fundamental group; Covering spaces; Introduction to homology and manifolds''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-topology-topological-space> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''topological space''' ;
  skos:definition '''A set X with a topology τ (a collection of open sets) satisfying: ∅ and X are open, arbitrary unions of open sets are open, and finite intersections of open sets are open.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-topology-homeomorphism> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''homeomorphism''' ;
  skos:definition '''A bijection f: X → Y such that both f and f⁻¹ are continuous; X and Y are topologically identical.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-topology-topological-invariant> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''topological invariant''' ;
  skos:definition '''A property preserved by homeomorphism, e.g., compactness, connectedness, Betti numbers.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-topology-connected-space> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''connected space''' ;
  skos:definition '''A topological space that cannot be partitioned into two disjoint nonempty open sets.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-topology-compact-space> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''compact space''' ;
  skos:definition '''A topological space where every open cover has a finite subcover.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-topology-hausdorff-space-t> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Hausdorff space (T₂)''' ;
  skos:definition '''A space where any two distinct points have disjoint open neighborhoods; metric spaces are Hausdorff.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-topology-homotopy> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''homotopy''' ;
  skos:definition '''A continuous deformation of one continuous map into another; f, g: X→Y are homotopic if there exists H: X×[0,1]→Y with H(x,0)=f(x) and H(x,1)=g(x).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-topology-fundamental-group-x-x> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''fundamental group π₁(X, x₀)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The group of homotopy classes of loops based at x₀ in X, with concatenation as the group operation; measures 1-dimensional 'holes'.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-topology-simply-connected> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''simply connected''' ;
  skos:definition '''A path-connected space with trivial fundamental group (π₁ = {e}); every loop is contractible to a point.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-mathematics-topology-covering-space> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''covering space''' ;
  skos:definition '''A space X̃ with a surjection p: X̃ → X such that every point of X has an open neighborhood U whose preimage is a disjoint union of copies of U.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-topology-tychonoff-s-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Tychonoff's theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''An arbitrary product of compact topological spaces is compact (in the product topology).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-topology-urysohn-s-lemma> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Urysohn's lemma''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''In a normal space (T₄), for any two disjoint closed sets A and B, there exists a continuous f: X → [0,1] with f|_A = 0 and f|_B = 1.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-topology-urysohn-metrization-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Urysohn metrization theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every second-countable T₃ (regular Hausdorff) space is metrizable.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-topology-seifert-van-kampen-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Seifert-van Kampen theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If X = U ∪ V with U, V, U∩V open and path-connected, then π₁(X) ≅ π₁(U) *_{π₁(U∩V)} π₁(V) (amalgamated free product).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-topology-brouwer-fixed-point-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Brouwer fixed-point theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every continuous function f: Dⁿ → Dⁿ from the closed n-disk to itself has a fixed point.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-topology-classification-of-compact-surfaces> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Classification of compact surfaces''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every compact connected surface is homeomorphic to either S², the connected sum of g tori (genus g), or the connected sum of k projective planes.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-topology-invariance-of-domain> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Invariance of domain''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If U ⊆ ℝⁿ is open and f: U → ℝⁿ is continuous and injective, then f(U) is open and f is a homeomorphism onto f(U).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-mathematics-topology-borsuk-ulam-theorem> a math:Equation ;
  rdfs:label '''Borsuk-Ulam theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''For every continuous f: Sⁿ → ℝⁿ, there exists x such that f(x) = f(-x); some two antipodal points map to the same point.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-mathematics-topology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .

### Domain: biology
