<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> skos:scopeNote '''Prokaryotic vs. eukaryotic cells; Cell membrane structure and function; Organelle structure and function; Cell transport mechanisms; Cell cycle and mitosis; Meiosis and gametogenesis; Cell signaling and communication; Extracellular matrix and cell junctions''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-plasma-membrane> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''plasma membrane''' ;
  skos:definition '''The phospholipid bilayer that encloses all cells, regulates transport, and mediates cell signaling.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-nucleus> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''nucleus''' ;
  skos:definition '''Membrane-bound organelle in eukaryotes that houses the cell's DNA and serves as the site of transcription.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-mitochondria> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''mitochondria''' ;
  skos:definition '''Double-membrane organelles that are the primary site of aerobic ATP production via oxidative phosphorylation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-endoplasmic-reticulum> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''endoplasmic reticulum''' ;
  skos:definition '''Network of membranes involved in protein synthesis (rough ER) and lipid synthesis and detoxification (smooth ER).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-golgi-apparatus> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Golgi apparatus''' ;
  skos:definition '''Organelle that receives, modifies, sorts, and packages proteins and lipids for secretion or delivery to other organelles.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-lysosome> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''lysosome''' ;
  skos:definition '''Organelle containing hydrolytic enzymes that degrade macromolecules and cellular debris at low pH.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-ribosome> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''ribosome''' ;
  skos:definition '''Ribonucleoprotein complex (large and small subunits) that catalyzes translation of mRNA into protein.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-cytoskeleton> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''cytoskeleton''' ;
  skos:definition '''Network of microfilaments (actin), intermediate filaments, and microtubules that maintains cell shape and enables movement.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-osmosis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''osmosis''' ;
  skos:definition '''Passive diffusion of water across a semipermeable membrane from a region of lower solute concentration to higher solute concentration.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-active-transport> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''active transport''' ;
  skos:definition '''Movement of molecules against their concentration gradient, requiring energy (ATP) and specific carrier proteins.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-cell-cycle> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''cell cycle''' ;
  skos:definition '''Ordered sequence of events (G1, S, G2, M) by which a cell grows and divides into two daughter cells.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-cytokinesis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''cytokinesis''' ;
  skos:definition '''Division of the cytoplasm following nuclear division, producing two separate daughter cells.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-cell-biology-tight-junction> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''tight junction''' ;
  skos:definition '''Cell-cell junction that creates an impermeable seal between epithelial cells, preventing paracellular transport.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-cell-biology-fluid-mosaic-model> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Fluid mosaic model''' ;
  skos:definition '''The plasma membrane is a dynamic, selectively permeable phospholipid bilayer with embedded proteins that can move laterally.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-cell-biology-mitosis-stages> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Mitosis stages''' ;
  skos:definition '''Prophase → Metaphase → Anaphase → Telophase → Cytokinesis; produces two genetically identical diploid daughter cells.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-cell-biology-meiosis-overview> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Meiosis overview''' ;
  skos:definition '''Two sequential divisions (Meiosis I: homolog separation; Meiosis II: sister chromatid separation) producing four genetically unique haploid gametes.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-cell-biology-endosymbiotic-theory> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Endosymbiotic theory''' ;
  skos:definition '''Mitochondria and chloroplasts arose from ancestral prokaryotes engulfed by a host cell; evidenced by double membranes, circular DNA, and 70S ribosomes.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-cell-biology-vesicular-trafficking> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Vesicular trafficking''' ;
  skos:definition '''Proteins synthesized on rough ER are packaged into vesicles, modified in the Golgi (cis → medial → trans), and dispatched to lysosomes, plasma membrane, or extracellular space.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-cell-biology-passive-vs-active-transport> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Passive vs. active transport''' ;
  skos:definition '''Passive (diffusion, facilitated diffusion, osmosis): down concentration gradient, no ATP. Active: against gradient, requires ATP (primary) or gradient (secondary).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-cell-biology-signal-transduction-cascade> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Signal transduction cascade''' ;
  skos:definition '''Extracellular ligand binds receptor → intracellular second messengers (cAMP, Ca²⁺, IP3) → kinase cascades → gene expression or metabolic changes.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-cell-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Biochemistry and Metabolism''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
