<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> skos:scopeNote '''Enzyme kinetics and inhibition; Glycolysis; Citric acid cycle (Krebs cycle); Oxidative phosphorylation and electron transport chain; Gluconeogenesis and glycogen metabolism; Fatty acid oxidation and synthesis; Amino acid metabolism; Metabolic regulation and integration''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-enzyme> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''enzyme''' ;
  skos:definition '''A biological catalyst (usually protein) that accelerates chemical reactions by lowering activation energy without being consumed.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-substrate> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''substrate''' ;
  skos:definition '''The specific molecule upon which an enzyme acts, binding at the active site.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-km-michaelis-constant> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Km (Michaelis constant)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The substrate concentration at which reaction velocity is half of Vmax; reflects enzyme-substrate affinity (lower Km = higher affinity).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-vmax> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Vmax''' ;
  skos:definition '''The maximum reaction velocity achieved when all enzyme active sites are saturated with substrate.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-competitive-inhibition> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''competitive inhibition''' ;
  skos:definition '''Inhibitor resembles substrate and binds reversibly to the active site; raises apparent Km, Vmax unchanged; overcome by increasing substrate.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-allosteric-regulation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''allosteric regulation''' ;
  skos:definition '''Regulation of enzyme activity by a molecule binding to a site other than the active site, causing conformational change.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-atp> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''ATP''' ;
  skos:definition '''Adenosine triphosphate; the primary cellular energy currency, releasing energy upon hydrolysis of its terminal phosphate bond.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-nad-nadh> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''NAD+/NADH''' ;
  skos:definition '''Nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide; electron carrier that accepts (NAD+ → NADH) or donates electrons (NADH → NAD+) in metabolic reactions.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-glycolysis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''glycolysis''' ;
  skos:definition '''The ten-step cytoplasmic pathway that converts one glucose into two pyruvate, yielding a net 2 ATP and 2 NADH.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-oxidative-phosphorylation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''oxidative phosphorylation''' ;
  skos:definition '''The mitochondrial process coupling electron transfer through the ETC to ATP synthesis via ATP synthase, driven by the proton gradient.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-beta-oxidation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''beta-oxidation''' ;
  skos:definition '''The mitochondrial process that sequentially cleaves two-carbon acetyl-CoA units from fatty acids, generating NADH, FADH2, and acetyl-CoA.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-gluconeogenesis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''gluconeogenesis''' ;
  skos:definition '''Synthesis of glucose from non-carbohydrate precursors (pyruvate, lactate, glycerol, amino acids), primarily in the liver.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-feedback-inhibition> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''feedback inhibition''' ;
  skos:definition '''Regulation in which the end product of a metabolic pathway inhibits an earlier enzyme in the same pathway.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-michaelis-menten-equation> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Michaelis-Menten equation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''v = Vmax[S] / (Km + [S])''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-glycolysis-net-reaction> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Glycolysis net reaction''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Glucose + 2 NAD⁺ + 2 ADP + 2 Pi → 2 Pyruvate + 2 NADH + 2 ATP + 2 H₂O''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-citric-acid-cycle-tca-cycle> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Citric acid cycle (TCA cycle)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Acetyl-CoA enters, condenses with oxaloacetate → citrate; 8 steps yield 3 NADH, 1 FADH2, 1 GTP per turn; CO2 released; oxaloacetate regenerated.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-electron-transport-chain> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Electron transport chain''' ;
  skos:definition '''NADH and FADH2 donate electrons to Complexes I–IV; electrons ultimately reduce O2 to H2O; proton gradient drives ATP synthase (Complex V); ~34 ATP per glucose.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-glucose-catabolism-atp-yield> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Glucose catabolism ATP yield''' ;
  skos:definition '''Complete oxidation of glucose: ~30–32 ATP (2 glycolysis + 2 TCA substrate-level + ~26–28 oxidative phosphorylation).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-competitive-vs-non-competitive-inhibition> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Competitive vs. non-competitive inhibition''' ;
  skos:definition '''Competitive: Km↑, Vmax unchanged. Non-competitive: Km unchanged, Vmax↓. Uncompetitive: both Km and Vmax↓.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism-metabolic-integration> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Metabolic integration''' ;
  skos:definition '''Fed state: insulin promotes glycolysis, glycogenesis, lipogenesis. Fasting: glucagon/epinephrine promote glycogenolysis, gluconeogenesis, lipolysis, beta-oxidation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-biochemistry-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-molecular-biology> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Molecular Biology''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-biology> ;
