<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> skos:scopeNote '''Fertilization and cleavage; Gastrulation and germ layer formation; Organogenesis; Cell fate determination and induction; Developmental signaling pathways; Stem cells and potency; Homeotic genes and body plan; Aging and senescence''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-developmental-biology-fertilization> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''fertilization''' ;
  skos:definition '''Fusion of a sperm and egg to form a diploid zygote, the single-celled precursor to the entire organism.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-developmental-biology-cleavage> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''cleavage''' ;
  skos:definition '''Rapid mitotic divisions of the zygote without growth, producing the morula and then the blastula/blastocyst.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-developmental-biology-gastrulation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''gastrulation''' ;
  skos:definition '''Morphogenetic process that converts the blastula into a three-layered gastrula (ectoderm, mesoderm, endoderm) through cell migration.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-developmental-biology-germ-layers> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''germ layers''' ;
  skos:definition '''Three primary cell layers formed during gastrulation: ectoderm (skin, nervous system), mesoderm (muscle, bone, blood), endoderm (gut lining, lungs, liver).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-developmental-biology-induction> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''induction''' ;
  skos:definition '''Process by which one group of cells (organizer) signals neighboring cells to change their developmental fate.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-developmental-biology-totipotent> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''totipotent''' ;
  skos:definition '''Capacity of a cell to develop into any cell type, including extra-embryonic tissues; only the zygote and early blastomeres are totipotent.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-developmental-biology-pluripotent> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''pluripotent''' ;
  skos:definition '''Capacity to differentiate into any cell type of the body proper but not extra-embryonic tissues; embryonic stem cells (ESCs) and iPSCs are pluripotent.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-developmental-biology-homeotic-gene> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''homeotic gene''' ;
  skos:definition '''A regulatory gene that specifies body segment identity during development; contains a homeobox encoding the DNA-binding homeodomain.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-developmental-biology-neural-tube> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''neural tube''' ;
  skos:definition '''Embryonic precursor to the brain and spinal cord, formed by folding of the neural plate ectoderm; failure to close causes anencephaly or spina bifida.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-developmental-biology-apoptosis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''apoptosis''' ;
  skos:definition '''Programmed cell death involving caspase activation, DNA fragmentation, and cell shrinkage; essential for development (e.g., digit sculpting) and tissue homeostasis.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-developmental-biology-morphogen-gradient> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''morphogen gradient''' ;
  skos:definition '''A diffusible signaling molecule whose concentration gradient provides positional information to cells, specifying different cell fates at different thresholds.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-developmental-biology-germ-layer-derivatives> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Germ layer derivatives''' ;
  skos:definition '''Ectoderm → epidermis, nervous system, sensory organs. Mesoderm → muscle, skeleton, circulatory system, kidneys, gonads. Endoderm → digestive and respiratory epithelium, liver, pancreas.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-developmental-biology-embryonic-induction-spemann-organizer> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Embryonic induction (Spemann organizer)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Dorsal lip of the blastopore (Spemann-Mangold organizer) secretes BMP antagonists (noggin, chordin) → permits neural fate in dorsal ectoderm; transplantation of organizer induces a second axis.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-developmental-biology-hox-gene-collinearity> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Hox gene collinearity''' ;
  skos:definition '''Hox genes are arranged in chromosomal clusters; gene order on chromosome mirrors expression pattern along anterior-posterior axis (spatial collinearity).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-developmental-biology-notch-delta-signaling-lateral-inhibition> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Notch-Delta signaling (lateral inhibition)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Cell expressing Delta ligand activates Notch on neighbor → cleaves NICD → NICD translocates to nucleus → activates target genes; produces alternating cell fate patterns.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-developmental-biology-wnt-hedgehog-and-bmp-pathways> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Wnt, Hedgehog, and BMP pathways''' ;
  skos:definition '''Wnt (via β-catenin), Hedgehog (via Gli TFs), and BMP (via Smad TFs) are conserved developmental signaling pathways used repeatedly for patterning and differentiation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-developmental-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Anatomy''' ;
  kcc:level '''intro''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> skos:scopeNote '''Anatomical terminology and body planes; Skeletal system; Muscular system and muscle contraction; Integumentary system; Digestive system anatomy; Reproductive anatomy; Lymphatic system; Nervous system gross anatomy''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-anatomy-anatomical-position> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''anatomical position''' ;
  skos:definition '''Standard reference position: body erect, facing forward, arms at sides with palms facing anteriorly.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-anatomy-sagittal-plane> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''sagittal plane''' ;
  skos:definition '''Vertical plane dividing the body into left and right portions; midsagittal (median) plane divides into equal halves.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-anatomy-sarcomere> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''sarcomere''' ;
  skos:definition '''The basic contractile unit of skeletal muscle, from Z-disk to Z-disk, containing overlapping thick (myosin) and thin (actin) filaments.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-anatomy-sliding-filament-theory> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''sliding filament theory''' ;
  skos:definition '''Muscle contraction mechanism: myosin heads bind actin, undergo power stroke (pivot), shorten the sarcomere by pulling thin filaments toward center; requires ATP and Ca²⁺.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-anatomy-periosteum> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''periosteum''' ;
  skos:definition '''The dense connective tissue membrane covering the outer surface of bones; contains osteoblasts, osteoclasts, and blood vessels for remodeling.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-anatomy-synovial-joint> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''synovial joint''' ;
  skos:definition '''Freely movable joint with a synovial cavity, articular cartilage, and synovial membrane secreting lubricating fluid; includes hinge, ball-and-socket types.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-anatomy-dermis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''dermis''' ;
  skos:definition '''The deep layer of the skin beneath the epidermis; contains collagen, elastin, blood vessels, sweat glands, hair follicles, and nerve endings.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-anatomy-villus-intestinal> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''villus (intestinal)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Finger-like projection of intestinal mucosa that increases surface area for nutrient absorption; epithelium contains enterocytes with microvilli (brush border).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-anatomy-meninges> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''meninges''' ;
  skos:definition '''Three protective membranes (dura mater, arachnoid mater, pia mater) surrounding the brain and spinal cord; CSF circulates in the subarachnoid space.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-anatomy-lymph-node> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''lymph node''' ;
  skos:definition '''Secondary lymphoid organ along lymphatic vessels that filters lymph, houses B and T lymphocytes, and initiates adaptive immune responses.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-anatomy-sliding-filament-model-of-muscle-contraction> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Sliding filament model of muscle contraction''' ;
  skos:definition '''Nerve impulse → ACh released → motor end plate depolarizes → Ca²⁺ released from SR → Ca²⁺ binds troponin → tropomyosin moves → actin sites exposed → myosin cross-bridge cycling → sarcomere shortens.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-anatomy-bone-remodeling> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Bone remodeling''' ;
  skos:definition '''Osteoclasts (bone resorption) and osteoblasts (bone deposition) continuously remodel bone; regulated by mechanical loading, parathyroid hormone (↑resorption), and calcitonin (↑deposition).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-anatomy-skin-layers> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Skin layers''' ;
  skos:definition '''Epidermis (keratinized stratified squamous; layers from deep to surface: stratum basale → spinosum → granulosum → lucidum → corneum) → dermis → hypodermis.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-anatomy-directional-anatomical-terms> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Directional anatomical terms''' ;
  skos:definition '''Superior/inferior (above/below), anterior/posterior (front/back), medial/lateral (toward/away from midline), proximal/distal (near/far from origin), superficial/deep.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-anatomy> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Plant Biology''' ;
  kcc:level '''intro''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> skos:scopeNote '''Plant cell structure and cell wall; Photosynthesis (light reactions and Calvin cycle); Plant organization: roots, stems, leaves; Water and nutrient transport (xylem, phloem); Plant hormones; Plant reproduction and alternation of generations; C3, C4, and CAM photosynthesis; Plant responses to the environment''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-plant-biology-chloroplast> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''chloroplast''' ;
  skos:definition '''Double-membrane organelle in plant cells that conducts photosynthesis; thylakoid membranes house the light reactions; stroma contains the Calvin cycle enzymes.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-plant-biology-photosynthesis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''photosynthesis''' ;
  skos:definition '''Process by which plants, algae, and cyanobacteria capture light energy to synthesize glucose from CO₂ and H₂O, releasing O₂.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-plant-biology-thylakoid> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''thylakoid''' ;
  skos:definition '''Flattened membranous sac within the chloroplast; stacked into grana; site of the light-dependent reactions and chlorophyll.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-plant-biology-stroma> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''stroma''' ;
  skos:definition '''Fluid-filled space of the chloroplast surrounding the thylakoids; site of the Calvin cycle (carbon fixation).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-plant-biology-xylem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''xylem''' ;
  skos:definition '''Vascular tissue that conducts water and dissolved minerals upward from roots; composed of dead tracheids and vessel elements; lignified walls.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-plant-biology-phloem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''phloem''' ;
  skos:definition '''Vascular tissue that transports photosynthate (sucrose) and other organic solutes bidirectionally; composed of living sieve tube elements and companion cells.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-plant-biology-transpiration> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''transpiration''' ;
  skos:definition '''Evaporative loss of water vapor from leaves through stomata; drives the transpiration-cohesion-tension mechanism for water ascent in xylem.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-plant-biology-stomata> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''stomata''' ;
  skos:definition '''Pores in the leaf epidermis surrounded by guard cells that regulate gas exchange (CO₂ in, O₂ and H₂O out) and transpiration.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-plant-biology-auxin> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''auxin''' ;
  skos:definition '''Plant hormone (indole-3-acetic acid) promoting cell elongation; responsible for phototropism and gravitropism; produced at shoot apical meristems.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-plant-biology-alternation-of-generations> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''alternation of generations''' ;
  skos:definition '''Plant life cycle alternating between diploid sporophyte (spore-producing) and haploid gametophyte (gamete-producing) generations.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-plant-biology-rubisco> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''RuBisCO''' ;
  skos:definition '''Ribulose-1,5-bisphosphate carboxylase/oxygenase; the enzyme that catalyzes carbon fixation in the Calvin cycle; the most abundant protein on Earth.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-plant-biology-photorespiration> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''photorespiration''' ;
  skos:definition '''The wasteful process in which RuBisCO adds O₂ instead of CO₂ to RuBP, consuming energy and releasing CO₂; minimized in C4 and CAM plants.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-plant-biology-photosynthesis-overall-reaction> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Photosynthesis overall reaction''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''6 CO₂ + 6 H₂O + light energy → C₆H₁₂O₆ + 6 O₂''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-plant-biology-light-reactions-photophosphorylation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Light reactions (photophosphorylation)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Photosystem II absorbs light → water oxidized → O₂ released → electrons pass through ETC → proton gradient → ATP synthase → ATP; electrons to Photosystem I → NADPH produced.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-plant-biology-calvin-cycle-dark-reactions> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Calvin cycle (dark reactions)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Carbon fixation: CO₂ + RuBP (C5) → 2× 3-PGA (via RuBisCO) → Reduction: 3-PGA → G3P (using ATP + NADPH) → Regeneration: G3P → RuBP (net 3 CO₂ → 1 G3P).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-plant-biology-c3-vs-c4-vs-cam-photosynthesis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''C3 vs C4 vs CAM photosynthesis''' ;
  skos:definition '''C3: CO₂ fixed directly by RuBisCO into 3-PGA; prone to photorespiration. C4: CO₂ pre-fixed as 4-carbon acid in mesophyll, concentrated in bundle sheath for RuBisCO. CAM: stomata open at night, CO₂ stored as malate, released by day; desert adaptation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-plant-biology-cohesion-tension-mechanism-for-water-transport> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Cohesion-tension mechanism for water transport''' ;
  skos:definition '''Transpiration pull at leaves creates tension → water cohesion (H-bonds) transmits tension down xylem column → water drawn up from roots; adhesion to xylem walls assists.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-plant-biology-plant-hormone-actions> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Plant hormone actions''' ;
  skos:definition '''Auxin: cell elongation, apical dominance, tropisms. Cytokinin: cell division, delays senescence. Gibberellin: stem elongation, seed germination. Abscisic acid (ABA): stomatal closure, dormancy. Ethylene: fruit ripening, leaf abscission.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-plant-biology> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Medical Genetics''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> skos:scopeNote '''Chromosomal abnormalities; Single-gene (Mendelian) disorders; Pedigree analysis; Multifactorial inheritance; Genomic imprinting; Pharmacogenomics; Cancer genetics; Genetic testing and counseling''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-medical-genetics-karyotype> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''karyotype''' ;
  skos:definition '''The complete set of chromosomes of a cell, arranged by size and morphology; used to detect chromosomal abnormalities.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-medical-genetics-aneuploidy> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''aneuploidy''' ;
  skos:definition '''Abnormal chromosome number due to nondisjunction; includes trisomy (47 chromosomes) and monosomy (45 chromosomes).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-medical-genetics-trisomy-21-down-syndrome> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''trisomy 21 (Down syndrome)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Presence of three copies of chromosome 21; most common viable autosomal trisomy; associated with intellectual disability, characteristic facial features, and heart defects.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-medical-genetics-autosomal-dominant-disorder> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''autosomal dominant disorder''' ;
  skos:definition '''A disorder caused by a single mutant allele (heterozygous sufficient); parent-to-child transmission (50% risk); each generation affected (e.g., Huntington's, Marfan syndrome).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-medical-genetics-autosomal-recessive-disorder> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''autosomal recessive disorder''' ;
  skos:definition '''A disorder requiring two mutant alleles; carriers are unaffected; 25% recurrence risk to offspring of two carriers (e.g., cystic fibrosis, sickle cell disease, PKU).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-medical-genetics-x-linked-recessive-disorder> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''X-linked recessive disorder''' ;
  skos:definition '''Disorder caused by a recessive allele on the X chromosome; primarily affects males (hemizygous); females are carriers; examples: hemophilia A, Duchenne muscular dystrophy.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-medical-genetics-nondisjunction> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''nondisjunction''' ;
  skos:definition '''Failure of homologous chromosomes or sister chromatids to separate during meiosis (or mitosis), producing aneuploid cells.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-medical-genetics-genomic-imprinting> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''genomic imprinting''' ;
  skos:definition '''Epigenetic phenomenon in which gene expression depends on the parent of origin; one allele is silenced by methylation; disruption causes Prader-Willi or Angelman syndrome.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-medical-genetics-oncogene> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''oncogene''' ;
  skos:definition '''A mutated/overexpressed proto-oncogene that drives uncontrolled cell proliferation; acts dominantly (gain-of-function); examples: RAS, MYC, HER2.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-medical-genetics-tumor-suppressor-gene> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''tumor suppressor gene''' ;
  skos:definition '''Gene that normally limits cell growth; both alleles must be lost or inactivated to contribute to cancer (two-hit hypothesis); examples: TP53, RB1, BRCA1.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-medical-genetics-lod-score> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''LOD score''' ;
  skos:definition '''Logarithm of odds score used in genetic linkage analysis; LOD > 3 considered significant evidence for linkage (1000:1 odds).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-medical-genetics-penetrance> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''penetrance''' ;
  skos:definition '''The proportion of individuals carrying a disease-causing allele who actually manifest the associated phenotype; incomplete penetrance complicates pedigree analysis.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-medical-genetics-autosomal-dominant-pedigree-pattern> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Autosomal dominant pedigree pattern''' ;
  skos:definition '''Trait appears in every generation; ~50% of offspring of an affected parent are affected; male and female equally affected; affected individuals usually heterozygous.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-medical-genetics-autosomal-recessive-pedigree-pattern> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Autosomal recessive pedigree pattern''' ;
  skos:definition '''Unaffected parents can have affected children (carrier × carrier → 25% affected); skips generations; consanguinity increases risk; equal sex distribution.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-medical-genetics-x-linked-recessive-pedigree-pattern> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''X-linked recessive pedigree pattern''' ;
  skos:definition '''Primarily males affected; affected males from carrier mothers; no father-to-son transmission; daughters of affected males are obligate carriers.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-medical-genetics-knudson-two-hit-hypothesis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Knudson two-hit hypothesis''' ;
  skos:definition '''Two mutational events required to inactivate both copies of a tumor suppressor gene; in hereditary cancers, first hit is germline (inherited), second is somatic; in sporadic, both are somatic.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-medical-genetics-common-chromosomal-trisomies> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Common chromosomal trisomies''' ;
  skos:definition '''Trisomy 21 (Down): intellectual disability, +21. Trisomy 18 (Edwards): severe, often lethal, +18. Trisomy 13 (Patau): severe defects, +13. 47,XXY (Klinefelter): infertility, tall stature. 45,X (Turner): short stature, gonadal dysgenesis.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-medical-genetics> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Nutrition and Metabolism''' ;
  kcc:level '''intro''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-biology> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> skos:scopeNote '''Macronutrients: carbohydrates, proteins, fats; Micronutrients: vitamins and minerals; Digestion and absorption; Energy balance and body weight regulation; Nutritional deficiencies and excesses; Diet and chronic disease; Metabolic disorders; Specialized nutritional needs''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-essential-nutrient> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''essential nutrient''' ;
  skos:definition '''A nutrient the body cannot synthesize in adequate amounts and must obtain from the diet; includes essential amino acids, fatty acids, vitamins, and minerals.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-essential-amino-acids> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''essential amino acids''' ;
  skos:definition '''The nine amino acids (His, Ile, Leu, Lys, Met, Phe, Thr, Trp, Val) that cannot be synthesized by the human body and must be obtained from diet.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-glycemic-index> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''glycemic index''' ;
  skos:definition '''A measure of how rapidly a carbohydrate food raises blood glucose relative to pure glucose (reference = 100); high GI foods cause rapid glucose spikes.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-basal-metabolic-rate-bmr> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''basal metabolic rate (BMR)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The minimum energy expenditure required to maintain basic physiological functions at rest in a thermoneutral environment; the largest component of total energy expenditure.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-vitamin> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''vitamin''' ;
  skos:definition '''Organic micronutrient required in small amounts for normal metabolism; classified as fat-soluble (A, D, E, K) or water-soluble (C, B vitamins).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-vitamin-d> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''vitamin D''' ;
  skos:definition '''Fat-soluble vitamin/prohormone; activated form (1,25-dihydroxycholecalciferol, calcitriol) promotes Ca²⁺ and phosphate absorption from gut; deficiency causes rickets (children) or osteomalacia (adults).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-iron-deficiency-anemia> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''iron deficiency anemia''' ;
  skos:definition '''The most common nutritional deficiency worldwide; inadequate iron reduces hemoglobin synthesis; symptoms include fatigue, pallor, microcytic hypochromic red blood cells.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-lipoproteins> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''lipoproteins''' ;
  skos:definition '''Protein-lipid complexes that transport cholesterol and triglycerides in the bloodstream; classified by density: chylomicrons, VLDL, IDL, LDL, HDL.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-nitrogen-balance> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''nitrogen balance''' ;
  skos:definition '''The difference between dietary nitrogen intake and excretion; positive balance (growth/pregnancy), negative balance (starvation, illness), zero balance (healthy adult).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-ketone-bodies> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''ketone bodies''' ;
  skos:definition '''Acetoacetate, beta-hydroxybutyrate, and acetone; produced in the liver from acetyl-CoA during prolonged fasting or carbohydrate restriction; alternative fuel for brain and muscle.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-antioxidant> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''antioxidant''' ;
  skos:definition '''Compound (vitamins C, E; beta-carotene; selenium; polyphenols) that neutralizes reactive oxygen species, reducing oxidative damage to cellular components.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-macronutrient-energy-densities> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Macronutrient energy densities''' ;
  skos:definition '''Carbohydrates: 4 kcal/g; Protein: 4 kcal/g; Fat: 9 kcal/g; Alcohol: 7 kcal/g.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-digestion-and-absorption-overview> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Digestion and absorption overview''' ;
  skos:definition '''Mouth (salivary amylase, mechanical) → stomach (pepsin, acid, protein denaturation) → small intestine (pancreatic enzymes, bile salts, brush-border enzymes) → major absorption in jejunum → large intestine (water, electrolyte reabsorption, fermentation).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-fat-soluble-vitamins-summary> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Fat-soluble vitamins summary''' ;
  skos:definition '''Vitamin A: vision, epithelium. Vitamin D: Ca²⁺ homeostasis, bone. Vitamin E: antioxidant, membrane. Vitamin K: coagulation (factors II, VII, IX, X). Deficiency risk with fat malabsorption.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-b-vitamin-coenzyme-roles> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''B-vitamin coenzyme roles''' ;
  skos:definition '''B1 (thiamine): TPP in TCA/glycolysis. B2 (riboflavin): FAD/FMN. B3 (niacin): NAD+/NADP+. B5 (pantothenic acid): CoA. B6 (pyridoxine): PLP in transamination. B9 (folate): 1-C transfers, DNA synthesis. B12 (cobalamin): methylation, nerve function.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism-insulin-and-glucagon-in-nutrient-homeostasis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Insulin and glucagon in nutrient homeostasis''' ;
  skos:definition '''Fed state: glucose ↑ → insulin ↑ → promotes glucose uptake, glycogenesis, lipogenesis, protein synthesis. Fasted state: glucose ↓ → glucagon ↑ → promotes glycogenolysis, gluconeogenesis, lipolysis.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-biology-nutrition-and-metabolism> ;
  kcc:canonType '''process''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .

