<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> skos:scopeNote '''Arrays and dynamic arrays; Linked lists (singly, doubly, circular); Stacks and queues; Hash tables and collision resolution; Trees (BST, AVL, red-black, B-tree); Heaps and priority queues; Graphs (adjacency list/matrix); Tries and suffix structures''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-data-structures-amortized-analysis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''amortized analysis''' ;
  skos:definition '''Method of analyzing algorithm cost averaged over a sequence of operations, smoothing out costly outliers (e.g., dynamic array doubling gives O(1) amortized push).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-data-structures-avl-tree> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''AVL tree''' ;
  skos:definition '''Self-balancing BST where for every node the heights of the two child subtrees differ by at most 1; guarantees O(log n) search, insert, delete.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-data-structures-red-black-tree> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''red-black tree''' ;
  skos:definition '''BST with one extra bit per node encoding color (red/black) and four structural invariants that guarantee O(log n) height.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-data-structures-b-tree> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''B-tree''' ;
  skos:definition '''Balanced search tree where each node can hold multiple keys and have multiple children; designed to minimize disk I/O, used in databases and file systems.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-data-structures-hash-collision> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''hash collision''' ;
  skos:definition '''Two distinct keys mapping to the same bucket; resolved by chaining (linked lists) or open addressing (linear/quadratic probing, double hashing).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-data-structures-heap-property> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''heap property''' ;
  skos:definition '''In a max-heap, every node's key is ≥ its children's keys; in a min-heap, ≤; guarantees O(1) peek at extremum.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-data-structures-load-factor> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''load factor''' ;
  skos:definition '''Ratio of stored elements to hash table capacity (n/m); kept below a threshold (e.g., 0.75) to maintain O(1) expected operations.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-data-structures-trie> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''trie''' ;
  skos:definition '''Tree where each node represents a prefix of stored strings; supports O(L) lookup, insert, and prefix search for strings of length L.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-data-structures-graph-adjacency-list> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''graph adjacency list''' ;
  skos:definition '''Graph representation storing, for each vertex, a list of its neighbors; space O(V+E), preferred for sparse graphs.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-data-structures-disjoint-set-union-find> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''disjoint-set (union-find)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Data structure tracking a partition of elements into disjoint sets; supports union and find operations, nearly O(1) amortized with union-by-rank + path compression.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-data-structures-dynamic-array-doubling> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Dynamic array doubling''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Append is O(1) amortized: total cost of n appends = O(n) by geometric series 1+2+4+...+n < 2n''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-data-structures-bst-search-complexity> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''BST search complexity''' ;
  skos:definition '''O(h) where h is tree height; h = O(log n) for balanced trees, O(n) worst case for unbalanced''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-data-structures-heap-insert-delete-min> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Heap insert/delete-min''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''O(log n) via sift-up / sift-down; build-heap from n elements = O(n) by summing height-weighted nodes''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-data-structures-hash-table-expected-operations> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Hash table expected operations''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''With uniform hashing and load factor α < 1, expected search time = O(1 + α) = O(1)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-data-structures-avl-rotation-invariant> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''AVL rotation invariant''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Single or double rotation restores balance in O(1); height h ≤ 1.44 log2(n+2)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-data-structures-union-find-with-path-compression-union-by-rank> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Union-Find with path compression + union by rank''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''m operations on n elements cost O(m · α(n)) total, where α is the inverse Ackermann function''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-data-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Algorithms & Complexity''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> skos:scopeNote '''Sorting algorithms (comparison, linear-time); Divide and conquer; Dynamic programming; Greedy algorithms; Graph algorithms (BFS, DFS, shortest paths, MST); Complexity classes (P, NP, NP-hard, NP-complete, PSPACE); Reductions and NP-completeness proofs; Randomized algorithms; Approximation algorithms''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-p> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''P''' ;
  skos:definition '''Class of decision problems solvable by a deterministic Turing machine in polynomial time.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-np> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''NP''' ;
  skos:definition '''Class of decision problems for which a YES-certificate can be verified by a deterministic TM in polynomial time; equivalently, solvable by a nondeterministic TM in polynomial time.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-np-complete> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''NP-complete''' ;
  skos:definition '''A problem X is NP-complete if X ∈ NP and every problem in NP is polynomial-time reducible to X; intuitively, the hardest problems in NP.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-np-hard> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''NP-hard''' ;
  skos:definition '''A problem to which every NP problem reduces in polynomial time; need not itself be in NP (e.g., HALT is NP-hard but undecidable).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-polynomial-time-reduction> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''polynomial-time reduction''' ;
  skos:definition '''A transformation f computable in poly-time such that x ∈ A iff f(x) ∈ B; written A ≤_p B; used to show hardness.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-dynamic-programming> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''dynamic programming''' ;
  skos:definition '''Algorithm design paradigm breaking problems into overlapping subproblems, solving each once, and storing results (memoization or bottom-up table) to avoid redundant recomputation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-greedy-algorithm> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''greedy algorithm''' ;
  skos:definition '''Algorithm that makes the locally optimal choice at each step; correct when a greedy-choice property and optimal substructure hold (proven e.g. by exchange argument).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-amortized-complexity> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''amortized complexity''' ;
  skos:definition '''Per-operation cost averaged over a sequence; potential method assigns a potential Φ to data structure states: amortized cost = actual cost + ΔΦ.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-approximation-ratio> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''approximation ratio''' ;
  skos:definition '''For a minimization problem, an algorithm has ratio ρ if it always returns a solution ≤ ρ · OPT; analogously for maximization.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-recurrence-relation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''recurrence relation''' ;
  skos:definition '''Equation defining the running time T(n) recursively in terms of smaller inputs, e.g. T(n) = aT(n/b) + f(n).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-pspace> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''PSPACE''' ;
  skos:definition '''Class of decision problems solvable by a deterministic TM using polynomial space; P ⊆ NP ⊆ PSPACE.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-co-np> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''co-NP''' ;
  skos:definition '''Class of problems whose complements are in NP; a problem is in co-NP if NO-instances have polynomial-time verifiable certificates.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-master-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Master theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''T(n) = aT(n/b) + f(n): (1) if f(n) = O(n^(log_b a - ε)) then T(n) = Θ(n^(log_b a)); (2) if f(n) = Θ(n^(log_b a) log^k n) then T(n) = Θ(n^(log_b a) log^(k+1) n); (3) if f(n) = Ω(n^(log_b a + ε)) and regularity holds then T(n) = Θ(f(n))''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-comparison-sort-lower-bound> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Comparison-sort lower bound''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Any comparison-based sorting algorithm requires Ω(n log n) comparisons in the worst case (decision-tree argument: n! leaves, height ≥ log2(n!)  = Ω(n log n))''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-dijkstra-s-algorithm> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Dijkstra's algorithm''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Single-source shortest paths for non-negative weights; O((V+E) log V) with binary heap, O(V log V + E) with Fibonacci heap''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-bellman-ford-algorithm> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Bellman-Ford algorithm''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Single-source shortest paths allowing negative weights; O(VE); detects negative cycles; relaxes all edges V-1 times''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-floyd-warshall-algorithm> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Floyd-Warshall algorithm''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''All-pairs shortest paths; O(V^3) DP: d[i][j][k] = min(d[i][j][k-1], d[i][k][k-1] + d[k][j][k-1])''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-kruskal-s-mst> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Kruskal's MST''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Sort edges by weight, add edge if it doesn't form a cycle (union-find); O(E log E); correctness by cut property''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-prim-s-mst> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Prim's MST''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Grow MST greedily from a root, always adding minimum-weight crossing edge; O(E log V) with binary heap''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-cook-levin-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Cook-Levin theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''SAT is NP-complete: every NP problem reduces to SAT in polynomial time; proof encodes TM computation as Boolean formula''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-mergesort> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Mergesort''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''T(n) = 2T(n/2) + Θ(n) → T(n) = Θ(n log n); stable; O(n) extra space''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-quicksort> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Quicksort''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Expected O(n log n) with random pivot; worst-case O(n^2); in-place (O(log n) stack space); not stable''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-radix-counting-sort> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Radix/Counting sort''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''O(n + k) time for integers in [0,k]; counting sort: count frequencies, compute prefix sums, place; radix sort: d passes of counting sort on each digit → O(d(n+k))''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-karatsuba-multiplication> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Karatsuba multiplication''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Multiply two n-digit numbers in O(n^(log_2 3)) ≈ O(n^1.585) using 3 subproblems of size n/2 instead of 4''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity-max-flow-min-cut-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Max-flow min-cut theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''In any flow network, max flow = min cut capacity; Ford-Fulkerson finds max flow in O(E · |f*|); Edmonds-Karp in O(VE^2)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-algorithms-and-complexity> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Computability & Automata Theory''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
