<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> skos:scopeNote '''Finite automata (DFA, NFA) and regular languages; Regular expressions; Context-free grammars and pushdown automata; Turing machines and computability; Decidability and undecidability; The halting problem and reductions; Chomsky hierarchy; Time and space complexity classes''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-dfa-deterministic-finite-automaton> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''DFA (deterministic finite automaton)''' ;
  skos:definition '''5-tuple (Q, Σ, δ, q0, F): states Q, alphabet Σ, transition function δ: Q×Σ→Q, start state q0, accept states F; recognizes exactly the regular languages.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-nfa-nondeterministic-finite-automaton> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''NFA (nondeterministic finite automaton)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Like a DFA but δ: Q×Σ_ε → P(Q); accepts if any computation path reaches an accept state; equivalent in power to DFA (subset construction converts).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-regular-language> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''regular language''' ;
  skos:definition '''A language recognized by some DFA; equivalently described by a regular expression; closed under union, concatenation, Kleene star, complement, intersection.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-pumping-lemma-regular> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''pumping lemma (regular)''' ;
  skos:definition '''For any regular language L, ∃ pumping length p such that any string s ∈ L with |s| ≥ p can be split s=xyz with |xy|≤p, |y|≥1, and xy^iz ∈ L for all i≥0; used to prove non-regularity.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-context-free-grammar-cfg> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''context-free grammar (CFG)''' ;
  skos:definition '''4-tuple (V, Σ, R, S): variables V, terminals Σ, production rules R of form A→α, start variable S; generates context-free languages.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-pushdown-automaton-pda> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''pushdown automaton (PDA)''' ;
  skos:definition '''NFA augmented with a stack; recognizes exactly the context-free languages; can be nondeterministic.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-pumping-lemma-cfl> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''pumping lemma (CFL)''' ;
  skos:definition '''For any CFL L, ∃ p such that any s ∈ L with |s| ≥ p can be split s=uvxyz with |vy|≥1, |vxy|≤p, and uv^ixy^iz ∈ L for all i≥0; used to prove non-context-freeness.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-turing-machine-tm> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Turing machine (TM)''' ;
  skos:definition '''7-tuple (Q, Σ, Γ, δ, q0, q_accept, q_reject) operating on an infinite tape; the canonical model of computation; computes exactly the recursively enumerable (RE) languages.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-decidable-language> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''decidable language''' ;
  skos:definition '''A language for which there exists a TM that always halts and correctly accepts or rejects every input; also called recursive.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-recognizable-language> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''recognizable language''' ;
  skos:definition '''A language for which some TM halts and accepts every string in the language, but may loop on strings not in it; also called recursively enumerable (RE).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-halting-problem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''halting problem''' ;
  skos:definition '''HALT_TM = {⟨M,w⟩ | TM M halts on input w}; undecidable (proven by diagonalization); RE but not co-RE.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-reduction-computability> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''reduction (computability)''' ;
  skos:definition '''A mapping reduction A ≤_m B: a computable function f where x∈A iff f(x)∈B; if B is decidable then so is A; contrapositively, if A is undecidable then B is undecidable.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-rice-s-theorem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Rice's theorem''' ;
  skos:definition '''Any nontrivial semantic property of Turing machine languages is undecidable; i.e., no algorithm can decide whether the language of an arbitrary TM has a nontrivial property.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-subset-construction-nfa-dfa> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Subset construction (NFA→DFA)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''States of DFA = subsets of NFA states; at most 2^n states; construction runs in O(2^n · |Σ|) time''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-myhill-nerode-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Myhill-Nerode theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''L regular ↔ index(≡_L) finite; min-DFA states = index(≡_L)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-church-turing-thesis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Church-Turing thesis''' ;
  skos:definition '''Every effectively computable function is computable by a Turing machine; not provable, but universally accepted as a definition of computability''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-diagonalization-halting-undecidability> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Diagonalization / Halting undecidability''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Assume TM H decides HALT_TM; construct D: on input ⟨M⟩, run H on ⟨M,⟨M⟩⟩, do the opposite → contradiction on D(⟨D⟩)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-chomsky-hierarchy> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Chomsky hierarchy''' ;
  skos:definition '''Type 0 (RE, TM) ⊃ Type 1 (context-sensitive, LBA) ⊃ Type 2 (CFL, PDA) ⊃ Type 3 (regular, DFA)''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory-cyk-algorithm> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''CYK algorithm''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Decides membership in CFL from CNF grammar in O(n^3 · |G|) time using DP table T[i][j][A] = true if A derives s[i..j]''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computability-and-automata-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Discrete Mathematics & Logic''' ;
  kcc:level '''intro''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
