<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> skos:scopeNote '''Propositional logic and Boolean algebra; Predicate logic and quantifiers; Proof techniques (induction, contradiction, contrapositive); Set theory and relations; Functions and cardinality; Combinatorics and counting; Graph theory fundamentals; Number theory and modular arithmetic''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-tautology> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''tautology''' ;
  skos:definition '''A propositional formula that is true under every truth assignment; e.g., p ∨ ¬p.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-satisfiability> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''satisfiability''' ;
  skos:definition '''A formula is satisfiable if there exists at least one truth assignment making it true; SAT is the canonical NP-complete problem.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-mathematical-induction> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''mathematical induction''' ;
  skos:definition '''Proof technique: establish base case P(0), then show P(k) → P(k+1) for all k ≥ 0; concludes P(n) for all n ≥ 0.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-strong-induction> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''strong induction''' ;
  skos:definition '''Assume P(0), P(1), ..., P(k) all hold, then prove P(k+1); equivalent in power to ordinary induction.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-bijection> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''bijection''' ;
  skos:definition '''A function that is both injective (one-to-one) and surjective (onto); establishes that two sets have the same cardinality.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-cantor-s-diagonalization> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Cantor's diagonalization''' ;
  skos:definition '''Proof that the reals are uncountable: for any enumeration of reals, construct a real differing from the n-th real in the n-th decimal place.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-modular-arithmetic> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''modular arithmetic''' ;
  skos:definition '''Arithmetic on residues mod n; a ≡ b (mod n) iff n | (a-b); forms the ring Z/nZ.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-euler-s-totient-n> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Euler's totient φ(n)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Count of integers in [1,n] coprime to n; φ(p) = p-1 for prime p; φ(mn) = φ(m)φ(n) if gcd(m,n)=1.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-pigeonhole-principle> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''pigeonhole principle''' ;
  skos:definition '''If n+1 objects are placed into n boxes, at least one box contains ≥ 2 objects; generalized: if kn+1 objects in n boxes, some box has ≥ k+1.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-graph-isomorphism> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''graph isomorphism''' ;
  skos:definition '''Graphs G and H are isomorphic if there is a bijection f: V(G)→V(H) preserving adjacency; not known to be in P or NP-complete.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-euler-path-circuit> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Euler path/circuit''' ;
  skos:definition '''Path/circuit visiting every edge exactly once; exists in undirected graph iff 0 (path) or 0 vertices (circuit) have odd degree.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-planar-graph> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''planar graph''' ;
  skos:definition '''Graph embeddable in the plane without edge crossings; by Euler's formula V - E + F = 2 for connected planar graphs.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-binomial-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Binomial theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''(x+y)^n = Σ_{k=0}^{n} C(n,k) x^k y^(n-k)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-inclusion-exclusion-principle> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Inclusion-exclusion principle''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''|A_1 ∪ ... ∪ A_n| = Σ|A_i| - Σ|A_i ∩ A_j| + ... + (-1)^(n+1)|A_1 ∩ ... ∩ A_n|''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-fermat-s-little-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Fermat's little theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''For prime p and a not divisible by p: a^(p-1) ≡ 1 (mod p); equivalently a^p ≡ a (mod p)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-euler-s-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Euler's theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''For gcd(a,n)=1: a^φ(n) ≡ 1 (mod n); generalizes Fermat's little theorem''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-euler-s-formula-planar-graphs> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Euler's formula (planar graphs)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''V - E + F = 2 for any connected planar graph; corollary: E ≤ 3V - 6 for simple planar graphs (V ≥ 3)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-de-morgan-s-laws> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''De Morgan's laws''' ;
  skos:definition '''¬(P ∧ Q) ≡ ¬P ∨ ¬Q; ¬(P ∨ Q) ≡ ¬P ∧ ¬Q; dual forms for sets: (A ∩ B)^c = A^c ∪ B^c''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic-chinese-remainder-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Chinese Remainder Theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If n_1,...,n_k are pairwise coprime, then for any a_1,...,a_k there exists a unique x mod (n_1...n_k) with x ≡ a_i (mod n_i)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-discrete-mathematics-and-logic> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Operating Systems''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> skos:scopeNote '''Processes and threads; CPU scheduling algorithms; Synchronization (mutexes, semaphores, monitors); Deadlock detection, prevention, avoidance; Memory management and virtual memory; File systems and storage; I/O and device management; System calls and kernel/user mode''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-operating-systems-process> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''process''' ;
  skos:definition '''A program in execution; has its own address space, PC, registers, open files, and OS state; isolated from other processes.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-operating-systems-thread> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''thread''' ;
  skos:definition '''Lightweight execution unit within a process; shares address space and file descriptors with other threads of the same process; has its own stack and registers.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-operating-systems-context-switch> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''context switch''' ;
  skos:definition '''OS operation saving the CPU state of a running process/thread and loading the state of another; overhead measured in microseconds.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-operating-systems-semaphore> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''semaphore''' ;
  skos:definition '''Synchronization primitive with integer value; P (wait/down) decrements and blocks if <0; V (signal/up) increments and wakes a blocked process; invented by Dijkstra.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-operating-systems-mutex-mutual-exclusion-lock> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''mutex (mutual exclusion lock)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Binary semaphore used to ensure only one thread executes a critical section at a time; provides ownership semantics.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-operating-systems-deadlock> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''deadlock''' ;
  skos:definition '''Circular wait among processes where each holds a resource another needs; necessary conditions (Coffman): mutual exclusion, hold-and-wait, no preemption, circular wait.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-operating-systems-banker-s-algorithm> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Banker's algorithm''' ;
  skos:definition '''Deadlock avoidance algorithm by Dijkstra; grants resource requests only if remaining allocation leaves the system in a safe state (where all processes can finish sequentially).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-operating-systems-virtual-memory> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''virtual memory''' ;
  skos:definition '''Abstraction giving each process a private large address space implemented by mapping virtual pages to physical frames; enables demand paging and isolation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-operating-systems-page-fault> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''page fault''' ;
  skos:definition '''Trap raised when a process accesses a virtual page not currently in physical memory; OS handles by loading the page from disk (demand paging).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-operating-systems-tlb-translation-lookaside-buffer> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''TLB (translation lookaside buffer)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Hardware cache for recent virtual-to-physical address translations; hit avoids page table walk; managed by OS on a TLB miss (software-managed) or hardware.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-operating-systems-inode> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''inode''' ;
  skos:definition '''Unix file system data structure storing file metadata (permissions, timestamps, size, pointers to data blocks) but not the filename.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-operating-systems-round-robin-scheduling> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''round-robin scheduling''' ;
  skos:definition '''CPU scheduling where each process gets a fixed time quantum in circular order; preemptive; fair but causes many context switches if quantum is too small.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-operating-systems-peterson-s-algorithm-2-process-mutex> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Peterson's algorithm (2-process mutex)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Uses flag[i] and turn variables; satisfies mutual exclusion, progress, bounded waiting for 2 processes on a sequentially consistent memory model''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-operating-systems-producer-consumer-with-semaphores> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Producer-consumer with semaphores''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''full=0, empty=N, mutex=1; producer: P(empty),P(mutex),add,V(mutex),V(full); consumer: P(full),P(mutex),remove,V(mutex),V(empty)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-operating-systems-dining-philosophers-monitor-solution> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Dining philosophers (monitor solution)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Each philosopher picks up both forks atomically inside a monitor; condition variables used to wait when a fork is unavailable; avoids deadlock''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-operating-systems-lru-page-replacement> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''LRU page replacement''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Evict the page whose most recent use was furthest in the past; optimal approximation; O(1) per access using doubly-linked list + hash map''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-operating-systems-optimal-page-replacement-belady> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Optimal page replacement (Belady)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Evict page not used for the longest time in the future; achieves minimum page faults; impractical online, used as benchmark''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-operating-systems-coffman-conditions-for-deadlock> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Coffman conditions for deadlock''' ;
  skos:definition '''Deadlock requires ALL of: (1) mutual exclusion, (2) hold-and-wait, (3) no preemption, (4) circular wait; remove any one to prevent deadlock''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-operating-systems> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Computer Networks''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> skos:scopeNote '''OSI and TCP/IP models; Physical and data-link layer; IP addressing, subnetting, routing; TCP and UDP transport protocols; Congestion control; DNS, HTTP, and application protocols; Network security (TLS, firewalls); Wireless and mobile networking''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-networks-osi-model> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''OSI model''' ;
  skos:definition '''7-layer reference model: Physical, Data Link, Network, Transport, Session, Presentation, Application; each layer provides services to the one above.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-networks-tcp-transmission-control-protocol> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''TCP (Transmission Control Protocol)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Connection-oriented, reliable, ordered byte-stream transport protocol; uses three-way handshake, sequence numbers, ACKs, and flow/congestion control.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-networks-udp-user-datagram-protocol> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''UDP (User Datagram Protocol)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Connectionless, unreliable transport protocol with minimal overhead; no handshake, ordering, or retransmission; used for DNS, video streaming, gaming.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-networks-ip-address> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''IP address''' ;
  skos:definition '''32-bit (IPv4) or 128-bit (IPv6) network-layer identifier for a host or interface; hierarchically structured to enable routing.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-networks-cidr-classless-inter-domain-routing> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''CIDR (Classless Inter-Domain Routing)''' ;
  skos:definition '''IP address allocation using variable-length subnet masks written as a.b.c.d/prefix; aggregates routes and reduces routing table size.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-networks-bgp-border-gateway-protocol> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''BGP (Border Gateway Protocol)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Path-vector routing protocol used between autonomous systems on the Internet; makes routing decisions based on paths, network policies, and rule sets.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-networks-ospf-open-shortest-path-first> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''OSPF (Open Shortest Path First)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Link-state intra-domain routing protocol; each router floods its link-state advertisements; runs Dijkstra to compute shortest paths.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-networks-tcp-three-way-handshake> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''TCP three-way handshake''' ;
  skos:definition '''Connection establishment: client sends SYN, server replies SYN-ACK, client sends ACK; establishes sequence numbers for reliable delivery.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-networks-congestion-window-cwnd> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''congestion window (cwnd)''' ;
  skos:definition '''TCP sender-side limit on unacknowledged bytes; increased in slow start (exponentially) and congestion avoidance (linearly); halved on packet loss.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-networks-dns-domain-name-system> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''DNS (Domain Name System)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Hierarchical distributed database mapping hostnames to IP addresses; resolvers query root, TLD, and authoritative name servers; uses UDP port 53.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-networks-tls-transport-layer-security> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''TLS (Transport Layer Security)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Cryptographic protocol providing authentication, confidentiality, and integrity over TCP; uses asymmetric crypto for key exchange, symmetric for bulk encryption.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-networks-nat-network-address-translation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''NAT (Network Address Translation)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Maps multiple private IP addresses to a single public IP using port numbers; breaks end-to-end connectivity; ubiquitous in IPv4 networks.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computer-networks-shannon-capacity> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Shannon capacity''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''C = B log2(1 + S/N) bits/second; C = channel capacity, B = bandwidth (Hz), S/N = signal-to-noise ratio''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computer-networks-nyquist-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Nyquist theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Maximum data rate = 2B log2(V) bits/s for noiseless channel with bandwidth B and V discrete signal levels''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computer-networks-tcp-slow-start> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''TCP slow start''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''cwnd starts at 1 MSS; doubles each RTT until ssthresh; then enters congestion avoidance (additive increase); on loss: ssthresh = cwnd/2, cwnd = 1 (Tahoe) or cwnd = ssthresh (Reno)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computer-networks-dijkstra-link-state-routing> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Dijkstra link-state routing''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Each router runs Dijkstra on full topology graph; O((V+E) log V); requires global topology knowledge via link-state flooding''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computer-networks-distance-vector-routing-bellman-ford> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Distance-vector routing (Bellman-Ford)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Each router maintains distance estimates to all destinations; exchanges with neighbors; d_x(y) = min_v{c(x,v) + d_v(y)}; susceptible to count-to-infinity''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-networks> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Databases''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> skos:scopeNote '''Relational model and SQL; Normalization (1NF, 2NF, 3NF, BCNF); Functional dependencies and keys; Transaction processing and ACID; Concurrency control (locking, MVCC); Query optimization and indexes; NoSQL and distributed databases; B-trees and storage structures''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-databases-relation-table> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''relation (table)''' ;
  skos:definition '''A set of tuples over a fixed schema (attribute names and domains); the fundamental structure in the relational model.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-databases-functional-dependency> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''functional dependency''' ;
  skos:definition '''X → Y holds if any two tuples agreeing on attributes X must agree on attributes Y; basis for normalization theory.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-databases-bcnf-boyce-codd-normal-form> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''BCNF (Boyce-Codd Normal Form)''' ;
  skos:definition '''For every non-trivial FD X → Y, X must be a superkey; eliminates all redundancy from FDs; may not preserve all dependencies.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-databases-3nf-third-normal-form> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''3NF (Third Normal Form)''' ;
  skos:definition '''For every non-trivial FD X → A, either X is a superkey or A is prime (part of some key); always achieves lossless join + dependency-preserving decomposition.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-databases-acid> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''ACID''' ;
  skos:definition '''Transaction properties: Atomicity (all-or-nothing), Consistency (valid state → valid state), Isolation (concurrent transactions appear serial), Durability (committed changes survive crashes).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-databases-serializable-schedule> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''serializable schedule''' ;
  skos:definition '''A concurrent transaction schedule equivalent to some serial execution of the same transactions; the gold standard for correctness.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-databases-two-phase-locking-2pl> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''two-phase locking (2PL)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Concurrency control protocol: transactions acquire all locks before releasing any (growing phase then shrinking phase); guarantees serializability.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-databases-mvcc-multiversion-concurrency-control> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''MVCC (multiversion concurrency control)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Each write creates a new version; readers access a consistent snapshot without blocking writers; used in PostgreSQL, MySQL InnoDB, Oracle.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-databases-b-tree-index> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''B+ tree index''' ;
  skos:definition '''Variant of B-tree where all data pointers are in leaves (linked for range scans) and internal nodes hold only routing keys; standard database index structure.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-databases-query-plan> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''query plan''' ;
  skos:definition '''The execution strategy chosen by the query optimizer, expressed as a tree of relational operators (scan, join, sort); cost estimated using statistics and cardinality.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-databases-cap-theorem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''CAP theorem''' ;
  skos:definition '''A distributed system can guarantee at most two of: Consistency, Availability, and Partition tolerance; formalized by Brewer and proven by Gilbert & Lynch.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-databases-wal-write-ahead-log> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''WAL (write-ahead log)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Durability mechanism: all changes are logged to stable storage before being applied to the data pages; enables crash recovery and REDO/UNDO.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-databases-armstrong-s-axioms> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Armstrong's axioms''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Reflexivity: Y⊆X → X→Y; Augmentation: X→Y → XZ→YZ; Transitivity: X→Y, Y→Z → X→Z; sound and complete for FD closure''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-databases-relational-algebra-operators> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Relational algebra operators''' ;
  skos:definition '''σ (select), π (project), ⋈ (natural join), × (Cartesian product), ∪, ∩, − (set ops), ρ (rename); complete basis for relational queries''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-databases-bcnf-decomposition> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''BCNF decomposition''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''While relation R has FD X→Y violating BCNF: decompose R into R1=(X∪Y) and R2=(R−Y+X); lossless but may not preserve all FDs''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-databases-2pl-serializability> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''2PL → serializability''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Any schedule produced by strict 2PL (hold locks until commit/abort) is conflict-serializable; the dependency graph is acyclic''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-databases-cap-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''CAP theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''In an asynchronous network, no distributed system can simultaneously guarantee Consistency, Availability, and Partition tolerance (proven by impossibility of linearizability under partition)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-databases> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Computer Architecture''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> skos:scopeNote '''ISA design (RISC vs CISC); Datapath and control unit; Pipelining and hazards; Cache memory hierarchy; Virtual memory and TLBs; Branch prediction; Out-of-order and superscalar execution; Memory consistency models''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-architecture-isa-instruction-set-architecture> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''ISA (instruction set architecture)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The interface between hardware and software defining the set of instructions, registers, addressing modes, data types, and memory model a processor implements.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-architecture-risc> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''RISC''' ;
  skos:definition '''Reduced Instruction Set Computer: simple, fixed-length instructions, large register file, load-store architecture, hardwired control; examples: MIPS, ARM, RISC-V.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-architecture-cisc> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''CISC''' ;
  skos:definition '''Complex Instruction Set Computer: variable-length instructions, memory operands, complex addressing modes, microcode; example: x86.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-architecture-pipeline-hazard> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''pipeline hazard''' ;
  skos:definition '''Condition preventing the next instruction from executing in its expected clock cycle; types: structural (resource conflict), data (RAW/WAW/WAR dependency), control (branch).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-architecture-raw-read-after-write-hazard> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''RAW (read-after-write) hazard''' ;
  skos:definition '''True data dependency: an instruction reads a register before a preceding instruction has written it; resolved by forwarding or stalling.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-architecture-cache-hit-miss> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''cache hit/miss''' ;
  skos:definition '''A hit occurs when requested data is found in cache (fast); a miss requires fetching from a slower memory level; miss types: compulsory, capacity, conflict.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-architecture-cache-locality> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''cache locality''' ;
  skos:definition '''Temporal locality: recently accessed data likely reaccessed soon; spatial locality: data near recently accessed data likely accessed soon; justifies caching.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-architecture-direct-mapped-cache> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''direct-mapped cache''' ;
  skos:definition '''Each memory block maps to exactly one cache line (index = address mod #lines); simple but prone to conflict misses.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-architecture-set-associative-cache> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''set-associative cache''' ;
  skos:definition '''Cache with k lines per set; a block maps to one set, can occupy any of k lines; k-way SA balances hit rate and hardware cost.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-architecture-amat-average-memory-access-time> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''AMAT (average memory access time)''' ;
  skos:definition '''AMAT = hit time + miss rate × miss penalty; fundamental metric for cache design.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-architecture-branch-prediction> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''branch prediction''' ;
  skos:definition '''Processor mechanism to guess the outcome of a branch before it is resolved; misprediction causes pipeline flush (penalty = pipeline depth).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-computer-architecture-out-of-order-execution> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''out-of-order execution''' ;
  skos:definition '''CPU executes instructions as operands become available rather than in program order; uses register renaming (Tomasulo algorithm) to avoid false dependencies.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computer-architecture-amat-formula> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''AMAT formula''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''AMAT = L1_hit_time + L1_miss_rate × (L2_hit_time + L2_miss_rate × DRAM_penalty)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computer-architecture-amdahl-s-law> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Amdahl's law''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Speedup_overall = 1 / ((1 - f) + f/s); f = fraction parallelizable, s = speedup of that fraction; limits parallel scaling''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computer-architecture-tomasulo-algorithm> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Tomasulo algorithm''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Dynamic scheduling with register renaming using reservation stations; eliminates WAR and WAW hazards; executes instructions out-of-order as operands arrive''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computer-architecture-pipeline-cpi> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Pipeline CPI''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''CPI = 1 + stall_cycles_per_instruction; ideal CPI=1 for single-issue pipeline; stalls from hazards and cache misses add fractional cycles''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computer-architecture-cache-size-associativity-tradeoff> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Cache size / associativity tradeoff''' ;
  skos:definition '''Miss rate generally decreases with size (capacity) and associativity (conflicts); direct-mapped fastest but most conflict misses; fully associative fewest misses but hardware cost O(n)''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-computer-architecture-memory-consistency-sequential> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Memory consistency (sequential)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Sequential consistency (Lamport): result of any execution is the same as if operations of all processors were executed in some sequential order; stronger than most hardware models''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-computer-architecture> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Programming Languages & Compilers''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> skos:scopeNote '''Lexical analysis (scanning, regular expressions); Parsing (LL, LR, recursive descent); Abstract syntax trees and semantic analysis; Type systems and type checking; Intermediate representations; Code optimization (dataflow analysis, SSA); Code generation and register allocation; Runtime systems (garbage collection, closures)''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-lexer-scanner> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''lexer (scanner)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Compiler phase converting a character stream into a token stream using regular expressions / finite automata; recognizes identifiers, literals, operators, keywords.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-parser> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''parser''' ;
  skos:definition '''Compiler phase constructing an abstract syntax tree from a token stream; verifies syntactic correctness; based on CFG; outputs an AST.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-ll-k-grammar> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''LL(k) grammar''' ;
  skos:definition '''Top-down parseable grammar using k lookahead tokens; FIRST and FOLLOW sets determine parse table; LL(1) is the most common.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-lr-k-grammar> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''LR(k) grammar''' ;
  skos:definition '''Bottom-up parseable grammar using k lookahead tokens; more powerful than LL(k); variants: SLR, LALR(1) (used in yacc/bison), canonical LR(1).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-ast-abstract-syntax-tree> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''AST (abstract syntax tree)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Tree representation of program structure after parsing; omits syntactic sugar; basis for semantic analysis, type checking, and code generation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-type-system> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''type system''' ;
  skos:definition '''Set of rules assigning types to expressions; a sound type system guarantees no type errors at runtime for well-typed programs (progress + preservation).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-static-vs-dynamic-typing> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''static vs dynamic typing''' ;
  skos:definition '''Static: types checked at compile time (Java, C, Haskell); dynamic: types checked at runtime (Python, JavaScript); gradual typing mixes both.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-ssa-static-single-assignment> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''SSA (static single assignment)''' ;
  skos:definition '''IR where each variable is assigned exactly once; uses φ-functions at merge points; simplifies many optimizations (constant propagation, dead code elimination).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-dataflow-analysis> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''dataflow analysis''' ;
  skos:definition '''Compile-time analysis propagating information along control flow graph edges to determine program properties; examples: live variables, reaching definitions, constant folding.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-register-allocation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''register allocation''' ;
  skos:definition '''Mapping of unlimited virtual registers to finite physical registers; modeled as graph coloring (interference graph); NP-complete in general, heuristics used.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-garbage-collection> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''garbage collection''' ;
  skos:definition '''Automatic memory management reclaiming unreachable objects; algorithms: reference counting, mark-and-sweep, copying, generational GC.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-closure> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''closure''' ;
  skos:definition '''First-class function paired with its captured environment (free variables); enables higher-order programming; implemented via heap-allocated environment record.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-first-follow-set-construction> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''FIRST/FOLLOW set construction''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''FIRST(α): terminals that can begin strings derived from α; FOLLOW(A): terminals that can follow A in some sentential form; used to build LL(1) parse tables''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-shift-reduce-parsing-lr> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Shift-reduce parsing (LR)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Parser maintains a stack; on each token either shifts (push) or reduces (pop RHS, push LHS); action/goto tables encode grammar; O(n) parse time''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-type-soundness-progress-preservation> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Type soundness (Progress + Preservation)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Progress: a well-typed term is either a value or can take a step; Preservation: if a well-typed term takes a step, the result is well-typed; together imply no stuck states''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-graph-coloring-register-allocation> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Graph coloring register allocation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Build interference graph (nodes=variables, edges=simultaneous live ranges); k-color for k registers; NP-complete; Chaitin's algorithm: simplify, spill, select''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers-reaching-definitions-dataflow> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Reaching definitions dataflow''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Forward analysis; gen[B] = defs in B not killed later in B; kill[B] = all defs of variables defined in B from other blocks; in[B] = ∪ out[pred]; out[B] = gen[B] ∪ (in[B] − kill[B])''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-programming-languages-and-compilers> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
