<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> skos:scopeNote '''Linear and logistic regression; Neural networks and backpropagation; Convolutional neural networks; Recurrent networks and attention / Transformers; Support vector machines; Decision trees, random forests, boosting; Unsupervised learning (k-means, PCA, EM); Generalization, bias-variance tradeoff; Reinforcement learning fundamentals; Probabilistic graphical models''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-bias-variance-tradeoff> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''bias-variance tradeoff''' ;
  skos:definition '''Test error = bias² + variance + irreducible noise; high bias = underfitting (model too simple); high variance = overfitting (model too complex); regularization and ensembles help.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-gradient-descent> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''gradient descent''' ;
  skos:definition '''Iterative optimization: θ ← θ − η∇L(θ); η is the learning rate; variants: SGD (one example), mini-batch, momentum, Adam.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-backpropagation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''backpropagation''' ;
  skos:definition '''Efficient computation of gradients in a neural network using the chain rule applied backward through the computation graph; O(forward pass) time.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-overfitting> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''overfitting''' ;
  skos:definition '''Model memorizes training data, failing to generalize; diagnosed by high train accuracy but high test error; addressed by regularization, dropout, data augmentation, early stopping.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-regularization> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''regularization''' ;
  skos:definition '''Adding a penalty to the loss to discourage complex models; L2 (ridge): +λ||w||², shrinks weights; L1 (lasso): +λ||w||_1, produces sparsity.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-svm-support-vector-machine> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''SVM (support vector machine)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Classifier maximizing the margin between classes; decision boundary defined by support vectors; kernel trick enables nonlinear boundaries implicitly in high-dimensional spaces.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-kernel-trick> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''kernel trick''' ;
  skos:definition '''Replaces dot products ⟨x,z⟩ with a kernel function K(x,z) = ⟨φ(x),φ(z)⟩, enabling nonlinear classifiers without explicitly computing high-dimensional feature maps.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-em-algorithm> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''EM algorithm''' ;
  skos:definition '''Expectation-Maximization: iteratively computes expected log-likelihood (E-step) and maximizes it over parameters (M-step); converges to local maximum; used for GMMs, HMMs.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-pac-learning> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''PAC learning''' ;
  skos:definition '''Probably Approximately Correct: a concept class is PAC-learnable if there is an algorithm that with probability ≥ 1-δ outputs a hypothesis with error ≤ ε using poly(1/ε, 1/δ, n) samples.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-vc-dimension> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''VC dimension''' ;
  skos:definition '''Largest set of points that a hypothesis class can shatter (classify in all 2^m ways); higher VC dimension = more expressive but more data needed for generalization.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-attention-mechanism> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''attention mechanism''' ;
  skos:definition '''Computes a weighted sum of value vectors, weights determined by compatibility between query and key vectors; enables Transformers to model long-range dependencies in O(n²) time.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-cross-entropy-loss> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''cross-entropy loss''' ;
  skos:definition '''L = −Σ_i y_i log(p_i); standard loss for classification; equivalent to negative log-likelihood under a categorical distribution; minimized by gradient descent.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-machine-learning-softmax-function> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''softmax function''' ;
  skos:definition '''σ(z)_i = exp(z_i) / Σ_j exp(z_j); maps logit vector to probability distribution; numerically stabilized by subtracting max(z).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-machine-learning-perceptron-update-rule> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Perceptron update rule''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''w ← w + y·x if misclassified (y·(w·x) ≤ 0); converges if data is linearly separable (Perceptron Convergence Theorem)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-machine-learning-logistic-regression-gradient> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Logistic regression gradient''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''L = −Σ[y_i log(σ(w·x_i)) + (1−y_i)log(1−σ(w·x_i))]; ∇_w L = Σ(σ(w·x_i)−y_i)x_i; convex → global minimum''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-machine-learning-backpropagation-chain-rule> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Backpropagation chain rule''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''∂L/∂w = ∂L/∂z · ∂z/∂w; gradients flow backward through computation graph; each layer needs local Jacobian; O(n) in network size''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-machine-learning-svm-primal-objective> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''SVM primal objective''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''min_{w,b} (1/2)||w||² subject to y_i(w·x_i + b) ≥ 1; soft-margin adds slack: +C Σξ_i; dual: max Σα_i − (1/2)Σα_iα_jy_iy_jK(x_i,x_j)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-machine-learning-bias-variance-decomposition> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Bias-variance decomposition''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''E[(y−f̂(x))²] = (Bias[f̂(x)])² + Var[f̂(x)] + σ²_noise; bias = E[f̂]−f; variance = E[(f̂−E[f̂])²]''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-machine-learning-vc-generalization-bound> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''VC generalization bound''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''With probability ≥ 1−δ: error(h) ≤ err_train(h) + √((VC(H)·ln(2m/VC(H)) + ln(4/δ)) / (2m)) for m training examples''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-machine-learning-k-means-algorithm> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''k-means algorithm''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Initialize k centroids; alternate: assign each point to nearest centroid, recompute centroids as cluster means; converges to local optimum; O(nkd) per iteration''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-machine-learning-pca-via-svd> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''PCA via SVD''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Center data X; compute SVD: X = UΣV^T; principal components = columns of V; project onto top-k: X_k = XV_k; captures maximum variance directions''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-machine-learning-transformer-self-attention> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Transformer self-attention''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Attention(Q,K,V) = softmax(QK^T / √d_k) · V; Q=XW_Q, K=XW_K, V=XW_V; multi-head: concat h heads, project; O(n²d) per layer''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-machine-learning> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Probability & Statistics for CS''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> skos:scopeNote '''Probability axioms, conditional probability, Bayes' theorem; Random variables (discrete and continuous); Expectation, variance, and moments; Common distributions (Bernoulli, Binomial, Poisson, Gaussian, Exponential); Concentration inequalities (Markov, Chebyshev, Chernoff bounds); Markov chains and steady state; Maximum likelihood estimation; Hypothesis testing and confidence intervals''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-bayes-theorem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Bayes' theorem''' ;
  skos:definition '''P(A|B) = P(B|A)·P(A) / P(B); relates conditional and marginal probabilities; foundation of Bayesian inference.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-expectation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''expectation''' ;
  skos:definition '''E[X] = Σ x·P(X=x) (discrete) or ∫x·f(x)dx (continuous); linearity: E[aX+bY] = aE[X] + bE[Y] always (no independence required).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-variance> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''variance''' ;
  skos:definition '''Var(X) = E[(X−E[X])²] = E[X²] − (E[X])²; Var(aX+b) = a²Var(X); Var(X+Y) = Var(X)+Var(Y) if X,Y independent.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-law-of-large-numbers> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''law of large numbers''' ;
  skos:definition '''Sample mean X̄_n → E[X] as n→∞ in probability (weak LLN) or almost surely (strong LLN); basis for Monte Carlo estimation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-central-limit-theorem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''central limit theorem''' ;
  skos:definition '''√n(X̄_n − μ) / σ → N(0,1) in distribution as n→∞; sample means of i.i.d. finite-variance variables are approximately Gaussian.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-markov-chain> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Markov chain''' ;
  skos:definition '''Sequence of random variables where P(X_{n+1}=j | X_n, ..., X_0) = P(X_{n+1}=j | X_n); memoryless; characterized by transition matrix P.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-stationary-distribution> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''stationary distribution''' ;
  skos:definition '''Distribution π such that πP = π; for ergodic chains, π is unique and the chain converges to π from any starting state.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-mle-maximum-likelihood-estimation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''MLE (maximum likelihood estimation)''' ;
  skos:definition '''θ̂_MLE = argmax_θ Σ log p(x_i; θ); finds parameter maximizing probability of observed data; consistent and asymptotically efficient under regularity conditions.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-p-value> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''p-value''' ;
  skos:definition '''Probability of observing a test statistic at least as extreme as observed, assuming the null hypothesis is true; small p-value (< α) → reject H_0.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-poisson-distribution> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Poisson distribution''' ;
  skos:definition '''P(X=k) = λ^k e^{-λ}/k!; models count of rare events in fixed interval; E[X]=Var(X)=λ; Poisson approximates Binomial when n large, p small, λ=np.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-markov-s-inequality> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Markov's inequality''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''For X ≥ 0: P(X ≥ a) ≤ E[X]/a; weakest but most general concentration bound''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-chebyshev-s-inequality> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Chebyshev's inequality''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''P(|X − μ| ≥ kσ) ≤ 1/k²; uses variance; P(|X−μ| ≥ t) ≤ Var(X)/t²''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-chernoff-bound> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Chernoff bound''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''For sum X = X_1+...+X_n of independent [0,1] r.v.s with mean μ: P(X ≥ (1+δ)μ) ≤ exp(−μδ²/3) for δ≤1; exponentially tight''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-law-of-total-expectation> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Law of total expectation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''E[X] = E[E[X|Y]]; equivalently E[X] = Σ_y E[X|Y=y]·P(Y=y)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-gaussian-normal-distribution> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Gaussian (Normal) distribution''' ;
  skos:definition '''f(x) = (1/√(2πσ²)) exp(−(x−μ)²/(2σ²)); N(μ,σ²); 68-95-99.7 rule: P(|X−μ| ≤ kσ) for k=1,2,3''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs-bayes-theorem-expanded> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Bayes' theorem (expanded)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''P(H|E) = P(E|H)·P(H) / [P(E|H)·P(H) + P(E|¬H)·P(¬H)]; posterior ∝ likelihood × prior''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-probability-and-statistics-for-cs> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Circuit Analysis''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> skos:scopeNote '''KVL, KCL, and Ohm's law; Node voltage and mesh current methods; Thevenin and Norton equivalents; Superposition and source transformation; Capacitors and inductors (transient analysis); RC, RL, RLC circuits; Operational amplifiers; Power and energy in circuits''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-circuit-analysis-kvl-kirchhoff-s-voltage-law> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''KVL (Kirchhoff's voltage law)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The sum of voltages around any closed loop in a circuit equals zero; a consequence of energy conservation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-circuit-analysis-kcl-kirchhoff-s-current-law> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''KCL (Kirchhoff's current law)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The sum of currents entering any node equals the sum of currents leaving; a consequence of charge conservation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-circuit-analysis-thevenin-equivalent> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Thevenin equivalent''' ;
  skos:definition '''Any linear two-terminal network can be replaced by a voltage source V_th in series with a resistance R_th; V_th = open-circuit voltage, R_th = resistance with independent sources zeroed.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-circuit-analysis-norton-equivalent> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Norton equivalent''' ;
  skos:definition '''Any linear two-terminal network can be replaced by a current source I_N in parallel with R_N; I_N = short-circuit current, R_N = R_th; I_N = V_th / R_th.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-circuit-analysis-superposition> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''superposition''' ;
  skos:definition '''In a linear circuit with multiple independent sources, the response is the sum of responses due to each source acting alone (others zeroed).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-circuit-analysis-capacitor> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''capacitor''' ;
  skos:definition '''Element storing energy in electric field; V = (1/C)∫i dt; i = C·dV/dt; impedance Z_C = 1/(jωC) in frequency domain; blocks DC, passes AC.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-circuit-analysis-inductor> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''inductor''' ;
  skos:definition '''Element storing energy in magnetic field; V = L·di/dt; i = (1/L)∫V dt; impedance Z_L = jωL; blocks AC, passes DC.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-circuit-analysis-time-constant> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''time constant τ''' ;
  skos:definition '''RC: τ = RC; RL: τ = L/R; time for exponential response to reach 1−1/e ≈ 63.2% of final value; system response ∝ exp(−t/τ).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-circuit-analysis-op-amp> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''op-amp''' ;
  skos:definition '''Operational amplifier: high-gain differential voltage amplifier; ideal: infinite input impedance, zero output impedance, infinite open-loop gain; used with negative feedback for precise circuits.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-circuit-analysis-impedance> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''impedance''' ;
  skos:definition '''Z = R + jX; generalization of resistance to AC circuits; Z_R = R; Z_C = 1/(jωC) = −j/(ωC); Z_L = jωL; Ohm's law: V = IZ in phasor domain.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-circuit-analysis-power-factor> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''power factor''' ;
  skos:definition '''cos(θ) where θ is the phase angle between voltage and current; PF=1 for purely resistive load; PF<1 for reactive loads; P = V_rms·I_rms·PF.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-circuit-analysis-ohm-s-law> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Ohm's law''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''V = I·R; R in ohms, I in amperes, V in volts; power P = VI = I²R = V²/R''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-circuit-analysis-kvl> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''KVL''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Σ V_k = 0 around any closed loop (sign convention: voltage rise positive or negative by convention)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-circuit-analysis-kcl> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''KCL''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Σ I_in = Σ I_out at any node; equivalently Σ_k I_k = 0 with consistent sign convention''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-circuit-analysis-thevenin-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Thevenin theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''V_th = V_oc (open-circuit voltage at terminals); R_th = V_oc / I_sc = resistance seen at terminals with independent sources zeroed''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-circuit-analysis-rc-transient-response> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''RC transient response''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''V_C(t) = V_f + (V_0 − V_f)·e^{−t/(RC)}; V_0 = initial voltage, V_f = final voltage; τ = RC''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-circuit-analysis-rlc-natural-frequency> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''RLC natural frequency''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''ω_0 = 1/√(LC); damping ratio ζ = R/(2)·√(C/L); overdamped ζ>1, critically damped ζ=1, underdamped ζ<1''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-circuit-analysis-inverting-op-amp-gain> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Inverting op-amp gain''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''V_out = −(R_f / R_in)·V_in; gain set by ratio of feedback to input resistor; virtual ground at inverting input''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-circuit-analysis-non-inverting-op-amp-gain> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Non-inverting op-amp gain''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''V_out = (1 + R_f/R_1)·V_in; input impedance ≈ ∞; output impedance ≈ 0''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-circuit-analysis-maximum-power-transfer> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Maximum power transfer''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Maximum power delivered to load when R_L = R_th (Thevenin resistance); P_max = V_th² / (4·R_th)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-circuit-analysis> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Signals & Systems''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> skos:scopeNote '''Continuous-time signals and systems; Convolution and impulse response; Fourier series and Fourier transform; Laplace transform and transfer functions; Discrete-time signals and z-transform; Sampling theorem and aliasing; Frequency response and Bode plots; Filter design (low-pass, high-pass, band-pass)''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-signals-and-systems-lti-system> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''LTI system''' ;
  skos:definition '''Linear Time-Invariant system: satisfies superposition (linearity) and output doesn't depend on absolute time (time-invariance); fully characterized by its impulse response h(t).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-signals-and-systems-convolution> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''convolution''' ;
  skos:definition '''(f * g)(t) = ∫_{-∞}^{∞} f(τ)g(t−τ)dτ; output of LTI system: y(t) = x(t) * h(t); discrete: y[n] = Σ_k x[k]h[n−k].''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-signals-and-systems-impulse-response-h-t> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''impulse response h(t)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Output of an LTI system when input is the Dirac delta δ(t); any LTI system output = input convolved with h(t).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-signals-and-systems-fourier-transform> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Fourier transform''' ;
  skos:definition '''X(jω) = ∫_{-∞}^{∞} x(t)e^{−jωt}dt; maps signal from time domain to frequency domain; inverse: x(t) = (1/2π)∫X(jω)e^{jωt}dω.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-signals-and-systems-laplace-transform> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Laplace transform''' ;
  skos:definition '''X(s) = ∫_0^{∞} x(t)e^{−st}dt; generalizes Fourier transform to complex s = σ+jω; converts differential equations to algebraic equations.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-signals-and-systems-transfer-function-h-s> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''transfer function H(s)''' ;
  skos:definition '''H(s) = Y(s)/X(s) for LTI system with zero initial conditions; ratio of Laplace transforms of output and input; encodes poles and zeros.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-signals-and-systems-nyquist-shannon-sampling-theorem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Nyquist-Shannon sampling theorem''' ;
  skos:definition '''A bandlimited signal with maximum frequency f_max can be perfectly reconstructed from samples taken at f_s ≥ 2·f_max (Nyquist rate); sampling below causes aliasing.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-signals-and-systems-aliasing> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''aliasing''' ;
  skos:definition '''Distortion when a signal is sampled below the Nyquist rate; high-frequency components appear as lower-frequency imposters; prevented by anti-aliasing (low-pass) filter before sampling.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-signals-and-systems-z-transform> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''z-transform''' ;
  skos:definition '''X(z) = Σ_{n=−∞}^{∞} x[n]z^{−n}; discrete-time analog of Laplace transform; H(z) = Y(z)/X(z) for DT-LTI systems.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-signals-and-systems-dtft-discrete-time-fourier-transform> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''DTFT (discrete-time Fourier transform)''' ;
  skos:definition '''X(e^{jω}) = Σ_{n=−∞}^{∞} x[n]e^{−jωn}; frequency representation of discrete-time signals; periodic with period 2π.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-signals-and-systems-bode-plot> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Bode plot''' ;
  skos:definition '''Log-frequency plots of magnitude |H(jω)| in dB = 20log10|H(jω)| and phase ∠H(jω) vs log(ω); asymptotic approximations use ±20dB/decade per pole/zero.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-signals-and-systems-convolution-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Convolution theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Multiplication in frequency domain ↔ convolution in time domain: F{x*h} = X(jω)·H(jω); F{x·h} = (1/2π)X(jω)*H(jω)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-signals-and-systems-fourier-transform-pairs-key> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Fourier transform pairs (key)''' ;
  skos:definition '''δ(t) ↔ 1; rect(t) ↔ sinc(ω); e^{−at}u(t) ↔ 1/(a+jω); cos(ω_0 t) ↔ π[δ(ω−ω_0)+δ(ω+ω_0)]; Gaussian ↔ Gaussian''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-signals-and-systems-parseval-s-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Parseval's theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''∫_{-∞}^{∞}|x(t)|²dt = (1/2π)∫_{-∞}^{∞}|X(jω)|²dω; energy in time domain = energy in frequency domain (up to 1/2π)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-signals-and-systems-laplace-transform-properties> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Laplace transform properties''' ;
  skos:definition '''Differentiation: L{x'(t)} = sX(s)−x(0); Integration: L{∫x dt} = X(s)/s; Shift: L{x(t−t_0)u(t−t_0)} = e^{−st_0}X(s)''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-signals-and-systems-nyquist-sampling-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Nyquist sampling theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''x(t) = Σ_n x[n]·sinc((t−nT)/T) if sampled at T ≤ 1/(2f_max); i.e., f_s ≥ 2B for bandwidth B''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-signals-and-systems-frequency-response-of-lti> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Frequency response of LTI''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''H(jω) = |H(jω)|·e^{j∠H(jω)}; output Y(jω) = H(jω)·X(jω); magnitude response = gain at each frequency; phase response = delay''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-signals-and-systems-fourier-series> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Fourier series''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''x(t) = Σ_{k=−∞}^{∞} c_k e^{jkω_0 t}; c_k = (1/T)∫_T x(t)e^{−jkω_0 t}dt; for periodic x(t) with period T=2π/ω_0''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-signals-and-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Control Systems''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> skos:scopeNote '''Open-loop vs closed-loop control; Transfer functions and block diagrams; Stability (poles, Routh-Hurwitz criterion); Root locus method; Frequency-domain methods (Bode, Nyquist); PID controllers; Steady-state error and system types; State-space representation''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-control-systems-open-loop-control> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''open-loop control''' ;
  skos:definition '''Control system where the output is not measured or fed back; simpler but sensitive to disturbances and model errors.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-control-systems-closed-loop-feedback-control> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''closed-loop (feedback) control''' ;
  skos:definition '''Control system where the output is measured and compared to the reference; error drives the controller; reduces sensitivity to disturbances and plant variations.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-control-systems-transfer-function-g-s> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''transfer function G(s)''' ;
  skos:definition '''G(s) = Y(s)/U(s) for a linear system; encodes dynamics as ratio of polynomials in s; poles = roots of denominator, zeros = roots of numerator.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-control-systems-pole> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''pole''' ;
  skos:definition '''Value of s where transfer function goes to infinity (root of denominator); determines system modes; poles with Re(s) < 0 → stable mode; Re(s) > 0 → unstable.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-control-systems-bibo-stability> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''BIBO stability''' ;
  skos:definition '''Bounded-input bounded-output stability: system is BIBO stable iff all poles have negative real parts; equivalently, impulse response is absolutely integrable.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-control-systems-routh-hurwitz-criterion> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Routh-Hurwitz criterion''' ;
  skos:definition '''Algebraic test for stability: construct Routh array from characteristic polynomial coefficients; system is stable iff all entries in first column are positive.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-control-systems-root-locus> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''root locus''' ;
  skos:definition '''Locus of closed-loop poles as gain K varies from 0 to ∞; starts at open-loop poles (K=0), ends at open-loop zeros or infinity; designed for transient response shaping.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-control-systems-pid-controller> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''PID controller''' ;
  skos:definition '''Controller with Proportional (K_p·e), Integral (K_i∫e dt), and Derivative (K_d·de/dt) terms; P reduces error, I eliminates steady-state error, D improves transient response.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-control-systems-gain-margin> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''gain margin''' ;
  skos:definition '''How much open-loop gain can increase before instability; GM = 1/|G(jω_pc)| in linear scale, where ω_pc is phase crossover frequency (∠G = -180°).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-control-systems-phase-margin> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''phase margin''' ;
  skos:definition '''Additional phase lag at gain crossover frequency (|G(jω_gc)|=1) before instability; PM = 180° + ∠G(jω_gc); good design: GM > 6 dB, PM > 30-45°.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-control-systems-steady-state-error> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''steady-state error''' ;
  skos:definition '''Error as t→∞ for a given reference input; e_ss = lim_{s→0} s·E(s) by Final Value Theorem; depends on system type (number of pure integrators in open-loop).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-control-systems-closed-loop-transfer-function> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Closed-loop transfer function''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''T(s) = G(s) / (1 + G(s)H(s)); forward path G(s), feedback H(s); sensitivity S = 1/(1+GH); complement T = GH/(1+GH)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-control-systems-routh-hurwitz-stability-test> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Routh-Hurwitz stability test''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Form Routh table from coefficients of char. polynomial a_n s^n + ... + a_0; system stable iff all entries in column 1 positive; # sign changes = # RHP poles''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-control-systems-final-value-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Final value theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''lim_{t→∞} f(t) = lim_{s→0} s·F(s); valid if limit exists and sF(s) has no poles on imaginary axis or RHP''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-control-systems-initial-value-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Initial value theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''lim_{t→0+} f(t) = lim_{s→∞} s·F(s); valid if f(t) has no impulses at t=0''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-control-systems-pid-transfer-function> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''PID transfer function''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''C(s) = K_p + K_i/s + K_d·s = (K_d s² + K_p s + K_i)/s; adds zero(s) to root locus to improve stability and response''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-control-systems-state-space-representation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''State-space representation''' ;
  skos:definition '''ẋ = Ax + Bu; y = Cx + Du; A: state matrix, B: input matrix, C: output matrix, D: feedthrough; eigenvalues of A = system poles''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-control-systems-nyquist-stability-criterion> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Nyquist stability criterion''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Z = N + P; Z = # closed-loop RHP poles, N = # clockwise encirclements of −1 by Nyquist plot, P = # open-loop RHP poles; stable iff Z = 0''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-control-systems> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Digital Logic & Boolean Algebra''' ;
  kcc:level '''intro''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> skos:scopeNote '''Boolean algebra and logic gates; Canonical forms (SOP, POS); Karnaugh maps and minimization; Combinational logic design; Arithmetic circuits (adders, multipliers); Sequential logic (flip-flops, latches); Finite state machines (Mealy, Moore); Programmable logic (PLAs, FPGAs)''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-boolean-algebra> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Boolean algebra''' ;
  skos:definition '''Algebraic structure with two elements {0,1}, operations AND (·), OR (+), NOT (¬); satisfies commutativity, associativity, distributivity, identity, complement, and absorption laws.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-minterm> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''minterm''' ;
  skos:definition '''A product term in which every variable appears exactly once (complemented or not); minterm m_i corresponds to the binary representation of i; SOP form = sum of minterms.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-maxterm> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''maxterm''' ;
  skos:definition '''A sum term in which every variable appears exactly once; POS form = product of maxterms; maxterm M_i corresponds to minterms with the same index.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-sop-sum-of-products> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''SOP (sum of products)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Boolean expression as OR of AND terms; canonical SOP = sum of all minterms where function = 1; can be implemented with two-level AND-OR logic.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-karnaugh-map-k-map> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Karnaugh map (K-map)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Grid-based minimization tool for Boolean functions; adjacent cells differ by one variable; groupings of 1, 2, 4, 8... cells give prime implicants.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-combinational-logic> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''combinational logic''' ;
  skos:definition '''Logic circuit whose outputs depend only on current inputs, not history; no feedback or state; implemented with gates; examples: adder, MUX, decoder.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-sequential-logic> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''sequential logic''' ;
  skos:definition '''Logic circuit with memory/state; outputs depend on inputs AND current state; implemented with flip-flops; examples: counters, registers, FSMs.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-d-flip-flop> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''D flip-flop''' ;
  skos:definition '''Edge-triggered storage element; Q follows D on rising clock edge; Q+ = D; used for registers and pipelines.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-mealy-machine> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Mealy machine''' ;
  skos:definition '''FSM where outputs depend on both current state and current inputs; output can change mid-state; generally fewer states than equivalent Moore machine.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-moore-machine> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Moore machine''' ;
  skos:definition '''FSM where outputs depend only on current state; outputs change only on state transitions; more predictable, used in most hardware FSM designs.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-don-t-care-condition> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''don't-care condition''' ;
  skos:definition '''Input combination that never occurs or for which output is irrelevant; can be assigned 0 or 1 to simplify Boolean expression; marked X in K-maps.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-hazard-glitch> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''hazard (glitch)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Momentary incorrect output in combinational logic due to different propagation delays along paths; static hazards (brief wrong constant), dynamic hazards (multiple transitions).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-de-morgan-s-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''De Morgan's theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''NOT(A AND B) = NOT(A) OR NOT(B); NOT(A OR B) = NOT(A) AND NOT(B); enables NAND/NOR universal gate implementation''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-boolean-identities> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Boolean identities''' ;
  skos:definition '''A+A=A, A·A=A (idempotency); A+1=1, A·0=0 (annihilation); A+0=A, A·1=A (identity); A+A'=1, A·A'=0 (complement); A''=A (double negation)''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-full-adder> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Full adder''' ;
  skos:definition '''Sum = A XOR B XOR C_in; Carry_out = (A AND B) OR (C_in AND (A XOR B)); 2-level logic; ripple-carry adder chains n full adders; O(n) delay''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-ripple-carry-vs-carry-lookahead> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Ripple-carry vs carry-lookahead''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Ripple: O(n) delay, O(n) area; Carry-lookahead: G_i = A_i·B_i, P_i = A_i+B_i; C_{i+1} = G_i + P_i·C_i; O(log n) delay with O(n log n) area''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-shannon-expansion-cofactor> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Shannon expansion (cofactor)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''f(x_1,...,x_n) = x_i · f_{x_i=1} + x_i' · f_{x_i=0}; basis for BDD-based CAD tools and multiplexer implementations''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''theorem''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra-quine-mccluskey-algorithm> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Quine-McCluskey algorithm''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Systematic tabular method to find all prime implicants and select minimum cover; equivalent to K-map minimization but algorithmic and scalable''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''algorithm''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-digital-logic-and-boolean-algebra> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Semiconductor Devices & Electronics''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-computer-science> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> skos:scopeNote '''Semiconductor physics (doping, p-n junction); Diodes and diode circuits; Bipolar junction transistors (BJT); MOSFETs and CMOS technology; Small-signal models and amplifier analysis; Frequency response of amplifiers; Logic families and noise margins; Power consumption in digital circuits''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-p-n-junction> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''p-n junction''' ;
  skos:definition '''Interface between p-type and n-type semiconductor; built-in potential V_bi = (kT/q)·ln(N_A·N_D/n_i²); under forward bias, current flows exponentially; reverse bias, small leakage.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-diode-equation-shockley> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''diode equation (Shockley)''' ;
  skos:definition '''I = I_0(e^{V/(nV_T)} − 1); I_0 = reverse saturation current; n = ideality factor (1-2); V_T = kT/q ≈ 26 mV at room temperature.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-bjt-bipolar-junction-transistor> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''BJT (bipolar junction transistor)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Three-terminal device (Base, Collector, Emitter); in active mode: I_C = β·I_B; I_E = (1+β)·I_B; controlled current amplifier; β (h_FE) typically 50-300.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-mosfet> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''MOSFET''' ;
  skos:definition '''Metal-oxide-semiconductor field-effect transistor; gate voltage controls channel; n-channel NMOS: I_D = μ_n C_ox (W/L)[(V_GS−V_th)V_DS − V_DS²/2] (triode); I_D = (μ_n C_ox W/2L)(V_GS−V_th)² (saturation).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-threshold-voltage-v-th> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''threshold voltage V_th''' ;
  skos:definition '''Gate voltage at which MOSFET channel inverts and current begins to flow; depends on oxide thickness, doping, and substrate bias.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-cmos-complementary-mos> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''CMOS (complementary MOS)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Logic family using pairs of NMOS and PMOS transistors; NMOS pulls output low, PMOS pulls output high; no DC current in steady state → low static power; standard for digital ICs.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-noise-margin> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''noise margin''' ;
  skos:definition '''NM_H = V_OH − V_IH; NM_L = V_IL − V_OL; measure of robustness against noise; CMOS: NM ≈ V_DD/2 for symmetric gates.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-transconductance-g-m> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''transconductance g_m''' ;
  skos:definition '''g_m = ∂I_D/∂V_GS = 2I_D/(V_GS−V_th) for MOSFET in saturation; g_m = I_C/V_T for BJT; key small-signal parameter relating input voltage to output current.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-small-signal-model> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''small-signal model''' ;
  skos:definition '''Linear approximation of transistor behavior around a DC operating point (Q-point); MOSFET: controlled current source g_m·v_gs with output resistance r_o = |V_A|/I_D; valid for small signal swings.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-dynamic-power-cmos> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''dynamic power (CMOS)''' ;
  skos:definition '''P_dynamic = α·C·V_DD²·f; α = activity factor (0-1), C = load capacitance, V_DD = supply voltage, f = clock frequency; dominant power consumption in digital ICs.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-diode-shockley-equation> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Diode Shockley equation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''I = I_S(e^{V_D/(nV_T)} - 1); V_T = kT/q = 25.85 mV at 300K; forward voltage drop ≈ 0.6-0.7V for Si at room temperature''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-mosfet-drain-current-nmos> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''MOSFET drain current (NMOS)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Triode: I_D = μ_n C_ox (W/L)[(V_GS−V_th)V_DS − V_DS²/2]; Saturation (V_DS ≥ V_GS−V_th): I_D = (μ_n C_ox W/2L)(V_GS−V_th)²(1 + λV_DS)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-bjt-current-relationships> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''BJT current relationships''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''I_C = β·I_B = α·I_E; I_E = I_B + I_C; α = β/(1+β); in active mode: V_BE ≈ 0.7V (Si); I_C = I_S·e^{V_BE/V_T}''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-cmos-inverter-switching-threshold> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''CMOS inverter switching threshold''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''V_M ≈ V_DD/2 for matched CMOS (equal drive strength); gate switches at midpoint; noise margins NM_H = NM_L ≈ V_DD/2 ideally''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-cmos-dynamic-power> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''CMOS dynamic power''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''P = α C_L V_DD² f; energy per switching event = C_L V_DD²; static leakage P_static = I_leak · V_DD becoming significant below 65nm''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics-miller-effect> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Miller effect''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Input capacitance C_in = C_gd(1 + g_m R_L); feedback capacitance C_gd is amplified by (1+gain) at input; limits high-frequency response of amplifiers''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-computer-science-semiconductor-devices-and-electronics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .

### Domain: economics
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-economics> a kcc:KnowledgeConcept ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Economics''' ;
