<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> skos:scopeNote '''Perfect competition: short-run and long-run equilibrium; Monopoly: pricing and deadweight loss; Price discrimination (1st, 2nd, 3rd degree); Monopolistic competition; Oligopoly: Cournot, Bertrand, Stackelberg; Natural monopoly and regulation; Market power and Lerner index; Concentration ratios and Herfindahl index''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-market-structures-perfect-competition> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''perfect competition''' ;
  skos:definition '''A market structure with many price-taking firms, homogeneous products, free entry/exit, and perfect information.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-market-structures-price-taker> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''price taker''' ;
  skos:definition '''A firm that takes the market price as given because it is too small to influence it; faces a perfectly elastic demand curve.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-market-structures-monopoly> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''monopoly''' ;
  skos:definition '''A market with a single seller of a product with no close substitutes, giving the firm market power over price.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-market-structures-market-power> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''market power''' ;
  skos:definition '''The ability of a firm to profitably set price above marginal cost.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-market-structures-lerner-index> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Lerner index''' ;
  skos:definition '''A measure of market power: L = (P - MC)/P = -1/|E_d|; ranges from 0 (perfect competition) to 1 (pure monopoly).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-market-structures-price-discrimination> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''price discrimination''' ;
  skos:definition '''Charging different prices to different customers for the same good, exploiting differences in willingness to pay.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-market-structures-cournot-competition> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Cournot competition''' ;
  skos:definition '''An oligopoly model in which firms simultaneously choose quantities, taking rivals' quantities as fixed.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-market-structures-bertrand-competition> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Bertrand competition''' ;
  skos:definition '''An oligopoly model in which firms simultaneously set prices; with homogeneous goods and equal costs, results in P = MC.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-market-structures-stackelberg-competition> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Stackelberg competition''' ;
  skos:definition '''An oligopoly model in which a leader firm moves first, choosing quantity, and a follower then best-responds.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-market-structures-monopolistic-competition> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''monopolistic competition''' ;
  skos:definition '''A market with many firms selling differentiated products, with free entry driving long-run profits to zero but P > MC.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-market-structures-natural-monopoly> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''natural monopoly''' ;
  skos:definition '''A market in which a single firm can serve the entire demand at lower cost than two or more firms, due to economies of scale.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-market-structures-herfindahl-hirschman-index-hhi> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Herfindahl-Hirschman Index (HHI)''' ;
  skos:definition '''A measure of market concentration: HHI = Σ s_i^2 where s_i is each firm's market share in percentage; ranges from 0 to 10,000.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-market-structures-perfectly-competitive-firm-s-profit-max> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Perfectly competitive firm's profit max''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''P = MR = MC in short-run; P = MC = min AC in long-run''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-market-structures-short-run-supply-curve-competitive-firm> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Short-run supply curve (competitive firm)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Firm supplies Q where P = MC(Q), for P ≥ min AVC; otherwise shuts down.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-market-structures-zero-profit-condition-long-run-competition> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Zero profit condition (long-run competition)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Free entry/exit drives π → 0; P = min LRAC''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-market-structures-monopolist-s-mr> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Monopolist's MR''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''MR = P(1 + 1/E_d) = P(1 - 1/|E_d|)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-market-structures-lerner-index> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Lerner index''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''L = (P - MC)/P = 1/|E_d|''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-market-structures-deadweight-loss-from-monopoly> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Deadweight loss from monopoly''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''DWL = (1/2)(P_m - MC)(Q_c - Q_m)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-market-structures-cournot-duopoly-symmetric-linear> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Cournot duopoly (symmetric, linear)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''a - bQ_1 - bQ_2 = MC; Best response: Q_i = (a-MC)/(2b) - Q_j/2; Nash: Q_i = (a-MC)/(3b)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-market-structures-bertrand-paradox> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Bertrand paradox''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''With homogeneous goods and equal costs, Bertrand competition yields P = MC even with only two firms.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-market-structures-first-degree-price-discrimination> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''First-degree price discrimination''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Firm charges each consumer their maximum WTP; extracts all CS; output equals competitive level (no DWL).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-market-structures-third-degree-price-discrimination-condition> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Third-degree price discrimination condition''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Optimal pricing across segments: MR_1 = MR_2 = MC; higher price in the less elastic segment.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-market-structures> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Welfare Economics and Externalities''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-economics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> skos:scopeNote '''Pareto efficiency and Pareto improvements; The fundamental theorems of welfare economics; Deadweight loss and market failure; Negative and positive externalities; Pigouvian taxes and subsidies; Coase theorem; Public goods: non-excludable and non-rival; Common resources and the tragedy of the commons; Second-best theory''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-pareto-efficiency> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Pareto efficiency''' ;
  skos:definition '''An allocation is Pareto efficient if no one can be made better off without making someone else worse off.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-pareto-improvement> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Pareto improvement''' ;
  skos:definition '''A reallocation that makes at least one person better off without making anyone worse off.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-externality> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''externality''' ;
  skos:definition '''A cost or benefit that affects a third party not involved in the market transaction, causing market failure.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-negative-externality> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''negative externality''' ;
  skos:definition '''A cost imposed on third parties by market participants; leads to overproduction relative to the social optimum.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-positive-externality> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''positive externality''' ;
  skos:definition '''A benefit conferred on third parties; leads to underproduction relative to the social optimum.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-pigouvian-tax> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Pigouvian tax''' ;
  skos:definition '''A corrective tax set equal to the marginal external cost, internalizing the externality and restoring social efficiency.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-social-marginal-cost> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''social marginal cost''' ;
  skos:definition '''Private marginal cost plus marginal external cost: SMC = PMC + MEC.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-coase-theorem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Coase theorem''' ;
  skos:definition '''If property rights are well-defined and transaction costs are zero, parties will negotiate to the efficient outcome regardless of the initial rights assignment.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-public-good> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''public good''' ;
  skos:definition '''A good that is both non-excludable (cannot prevent non-payers from consuming) and non-rival (one person's consumption does not reduce another's).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-free-rider-problem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''free rider problem''' ;
  skos:definition '''The tendency for individuals to under-contribute to public goods because they can benefit without paying.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-common-resource> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''common resource''' ;
  skos:definition '''A good that is non-excludable but rival in consumption; subject to overuse (tragedy of the commons).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-deadweight-loss> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''deadweight loss''' ;
  skos:definition '''The loss in total surplus from a market distortion (tax, externality, market power) relative to the efficient outcome.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-social-optimum-condition-with-externality> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Social optimum condition with externality''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''SMC = SMB; i.e., (PMC + MEC) = D(Q)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-optimal-pigouvian-tax> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Optimal Pigouvian tax''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''t* = MEC evaluated at the socially optimal quantity Q*''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-first-fundamental-theorem-of-welfare-economics> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''First fundamental theorem of welfare economics''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Every competitive equilibrium is Pareto efficient (given convexity and no externalities/public goods).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-second-fundamental-theorem-of-welfare-economics> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Second fundamental theorem of welfare economics''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Any Pareto efficient allocation can be achieved as a competitive equilibrium after an appropriate lump-sum redistribution of endowments.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-samuelson-rule-for-public-goods> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Samuelson rule for public goods''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Σ MRS_i = MRT; sum of individual marginal rates of substitution equals the marginal rate of transformation.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-coase-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Coase theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''With zero transaction costs and well-defined property rights, bargaining achieves the efficient level of an externality regardless of who holds the rights.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities-deadweight-loss-formula> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Deadweight loss formula''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''DWL = (1/2)(P_s - P_d)(Q_free - Q_taxed)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-welfare-economics-and-externalities> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Game Theory''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-economics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> skos:scopeNote '''Normal form and extensive form games; Dominant strategies and iterated elimination; Nash equilibrium; Mixed strategy Nash equilibrium; Backward induction and subgame perfect equilibrium; Repeated games and cooperation; Bayesian games and incomplete information; Auctions; Mechanism design basics''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-game-theory-nash-equilibrium> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Nash equilibrium''' ;
  skos:definition '''A strategy profile in which no player can increase their payoff by unilaterally deviating, given the strategies of all other players.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-game-theory-dominant-strategy> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''dominant strategy''' ;
  skos:definition '''A strategy that yields a higher payoff than any other strategy regardless of what opponents play.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-game-theory-mixed-strategy> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''mixed strategy''' ;
  skos:definition '''A probability distribution over pure strategies; a player randomizes to keep opponents indifferent.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-game-theory-subgame-perfect-equilibrium-spe> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''subgame perfect equilibrium (SPE)''' ;
  skos:definition '''A Nash equilibrium in which players' strategies constitute a Nash equilibrium in every subgame; found by backward induction.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-game-theory-backward-induction> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''backward induction''' ;
  skos:definition '''A method for solving extensive-form games by starting at the terminal nodes and working backward to determine optimal choices.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-game-theory-prisoner-s-dilemma> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''prisoner's dilemma''' ;
  skos:definition '''A symmetric two-player game in which the dominant strategy for each player leads to a collectively suboptimal outcome.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-game-theory-coordination-game> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''coordination game''' ;
  skos:definition '''A game in which players benefit from choosing matching strategies; typically has multiple Nash equilibria.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-game-theory-pareto-dominant-equilibrium> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Pareto dominant equilibrium''' ;
  skos:definition '''A Nash equilibrium that yields higher payoffs to all players than any other Nash equilibrium.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-game-theory-repeated-game> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''repeated game''' ;
  skos:definition '''A game in which the same stage game is played multiple times; repetition can sustain cooperation via punishment strategies.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-game-theory-folk-theorem> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''folk theorem''' ;
  skos:definition '''In infinitely repeated games with sufficient patience, any individually rational feasible outcome can be sustained as a subgame perfect equilibrium.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-game-theory-bayesian-nash-equilibrium> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Bayesian Nash equilibrium''' ;
  skos:definition '''A Nash equilibrium in a game of incomplete information in which each player maximizes expected payoff given beliefs about types.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-game-theory-auction-second-price> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''auction (second-price)''' ;
  skos:definition '''A Vickrey auction in which the highest bidder wins and pays the second-highest bid; truth-telling is a dominant strategy.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-game-theory-nash-equilibrium-definition> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Nash equilibrium definition''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''s* is a NE iff for all i: u_i(s_i*, s_{-i}*) ≥ u_i(s_i, s_{-i}*) for all s_i ∈ S_i''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-game-theory-mixed-strategy-indifference-condition> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Mixed strategy indifference condition''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''In a mixed NE, a player must be indifferent among all strategies played with positive probability.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-game-theory-prisoner-s-dilemma-payoff-structure> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Prisoner's dilemma payoff structure''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''T > R > P > S and R > (T+S)/2; defect is dominant for both, yielding (P,P) < (R,R).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-game-theory-subgame-perfect-equilibrium> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Subgame perfect equilibrium''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''SPE requires Nash equilibrium strategies in every subgame, not only on-path; eliminates non-credible threats.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-game-theory-minimax-theorem-zero-sum> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Minimax theorem (zero-sum)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''max_{x} min_{y} u(x,y) = min_{y} max_{x} u(x,y); value of zero-sum game is unique.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-game-theory-grim-trigger-strategy-repeated-games> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Grim trigger strategy (repeated games)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Cooperate until opponent defects; then defect forever. Cooperation is sustained if δ ≥ (T-R)/(T-P).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-game-theory-revenue-equivalence-theorem> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Revenue equivalence theorem''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Under standard conditions (symmetric independent private values, risk-neutral bidders), all standard auctions yield equal expected revenue.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-game-theory> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''GDP and National Income Accounting''' ;
