<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> skos:scopeNote '''Expenditure approach to GDP; Income approach and value-added approach; Nominal vs. real GDP and the GDP deflator; GDP vs. GNP vs. GNI; Components: C, I, G, NX; National saving and investment identity; Limitations of GDP as a welfare measure; Price indices: CPI and GDP deflator''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-gdp-gross-domestic-product> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''GDP (Gross Domestic Product)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The market value of all final goods and services produced within a country's borders in a given period.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-nominal-gdp> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''nominal GDP''' ;
  skos:definition '''GDP measured at current market prices without adjusting for inflation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-real-gdp> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''real GDP''' ;
  skos:definition '''GDP adjusted for price changes using a base-year price level; reflects actual changes in output volume.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-gdp-deflator> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''GDP deflator''' ;
  skos:definition '''A price index equal to (Nominal GDP / Real GDP) × 100; measures the overall price level of domestically produced goods.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-cpi-consumer-price-index> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''CPI (Consumer Price Index)''' ;
  skos:definition '''A price index measuring the cost of a fixed basket of goods and services purchased by a typical urban consumer.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-gnp-gross-national-product> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''GNP (Gross National Product)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The market value of all final goods and services produced by a country's residents, regardless of location: GNP = GDP + Net factor income from abroad.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-net-exports-nx> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''net exports (NX)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The value of exports minus imports; a component of GDP equal to X - M.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-national-saving> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''national saving''' ;
  skos:definition '''The total income in the economy not spent on consumption or government purchases: S = Y - C - G.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-investment-i> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''investment (I)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Expenditure on new capital goods, residential construction, and changes in business inventories.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-value-added> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''value added''' ;
  skos:definition '''The increase in the value of a good or service at each stage of production; GDP equals total value added across all sectors.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-expenditure-approach-to-gdp> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Expenditure approach to GDP''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''GDP = C + I + G + (X - M)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-national-income-identity-closed-economy> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''National income identity (closed economy)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Y = C + I + G  ⟹  S = Y - C - G = I''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-national-income-identity-open-economy> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''National income identity (open economy)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''S = I + NX  (or: S - I = NX = CA)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-real-gdp-calculation> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Real GDP calculation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Real GDP = Nominal GDP / GDP Deflator × 100''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-gdp-deflator> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''GDP deflator''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''GDP Deflator = (Nominal GDP / Real GDP) × 100''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-cpi-inflation-rate> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''CPI inflation rate''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''π_t = (CPI_t - CPI_{t-1}) / CPI_{t-1} × 100%''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-gdp-vs-gnp> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''GDP vs. GNP''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''GNP = GDP + Net factor income from abroad (factor payments received from abroad minus factor payments made to foreigners)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting-gdp-as-a-welfare-measure-limitations> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''GDP as a welfare measure: limitations''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''GDP omits household production, leisure, inequality, sustainability, and non-market activities; a rise in GDP does not necessarily imply a rise in welfare.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-gdp-and-national-income-accounting> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''IS-LM and AD-AS Models''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-economics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> skos:scopeNote '''IS curve: goods market equilibrium; LM curve: money market equilibrium; IS-LM equilibrium and comparative statics; Fiscal multiplier and crowding out; Liquidity trap (zero lower bound); Aggregate demand (AD) curve; Short-run aggregate supply (SRAS); Long-run aggregate supply (LRAS); Demand and supply shocks; Stagflation and the 1970s experience''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-is-curve> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''IS curve''' ;
  skos:definition '''The locus of (Y, r) pairs at which the goods market is in equilibrium (planned expenditure equals output); slopes downward in (Y, r) space.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-lm-curve> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''LM curve''' ;
  skos:definition '''The locus of (Y, r) pairs at which the money market is in equilibrium (money supply equals money demand); slopes upward in (Y, r) space.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-multiplier> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''multiplier''' ;
  skos:definition '''The ratio by which output changes in response to an autonomous spending change: k = 1/(1-MPC) in a simple Keynesian model.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-crowding-out> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''crowding out''' ;
  skos:definition '''The reduction in private investment caused by rising interest rates when expansionary fiscal policy increases government borrowing.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-liquidity-trap> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''liquidity trap''' ;
  skos:definition '''A situation in which interest rates are at or near zero, making monetary policy ineffective because people prefer to hold cash rather than bonds.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-aggregate-demand-ad> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''aggregate demand (AD)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The total demand for final goods and services in an economy at each price level; slopes downward due to the wealth, interest rate, and exchange rate effects.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-short-run-aggregate-supply-sras> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''short-run aggregate supply (SRAS)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The total supply of goods and services at each price level in the short run when nominal wages and prices of some inputs are sticky; slopes upward.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-long-run-aggregate-supply-lras> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''long-run aggregate supply (LRAS)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The total supply of goods and services at the natural rate of output (full employment); vertical in (Y, P) space.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-stagflation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''stagflation''' ;
  skos:definition '''The simultaneous occurrence of high inflation and high unemployment, typically caused by a negative supply shock.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-natural-rate-of-output> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''natural rate of output''' ;
  skos:definition '''The level of output consistent with full employment and the long-run equilibrium of the economy (potential GDP).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-mpc-marginal-propensity-to-consume> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''MPC (marginal propensity to consume)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The fraction of an additional dollar of income that households spend on consumption.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-goods-market-equilibrium-is> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Goods market equilibrium (IS)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Y = C(Y-T) + I(r) + G  ⟹  IS: r = f(Y) downward sloping''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-keynesian-expenditure-multiplier> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Keynesian expenditure multiplier''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''ΔY = ΔA / (1 - MPC) = k · ΔA; where k = 1/(1-MPC)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-multiplier-with-taxes> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Multiplier with taxes''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''k = 1 / (1 - MPC(1-t))''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-money-market-equilibrium-lm> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Money market equilibrium (LM)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''M/P = L(Y, r);  L_Y > 0, L_r < 0  ⟹  LM: r = g(Y) upward sloping''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-is-lm-simultaneous-equilibrium> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''IS-LM simultaneous equilibrium''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Solve IS and LM jointly for equilibrium (Y*, r*).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-ad-curve-derivation> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''AD curve derivation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''AD slopes downward: higher P → lower M/P → higher r (LM shifts left) → lower I and Y.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-tax-multiplier> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Tax multiplier''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''ΔY = (-MPC/(1-MPC)) · ΔT; tax multiplier is negative and smaller in absolute value than spending multiplier.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-balanced-budget-multiplier> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Balanced budget multiplier''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Equal increases in G and T yield ΔY = ΔG; the balanced budget multiplier equals 1.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models-long-run-self-correction> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Long-run self-correction''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''In ADAS model, a recessionary gap → falling wages → SRAS shifts right → Y returns to Y_n; no permanent output gap in long run.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-is-lm-and-ad-as-models> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> a kcc:Topic ;
