<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> skos:scopeNote '''Functions and forms of money; Money supply and the money multiplier; Central bank tools: reserve requirements, discount rate, open market operations; Quantity theory of money; Fisher equation and real vs. nominal interest rates; Inflation costs and seigniorage; Hyperinflation; Monetary transmission mechanism; Taylor rule''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-m1-money-supply> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''M1 money supply''' ;
  skos:definition '''The most liquid measure of money including currency in circulation and demand deposits (checkable deposits).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-m2-money-supply> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''M2 money supply''' ;
  skos:definition '''A broader money measure including M1 plus savings deposits, small time deposits, and money market mutual funds.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-money-multiplier> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''money multiplier''' ;
  skos:definition '''The ratio of the money supply to the monetary base: m = 1/rr (in simple model) or m = (1+c)/(rr+c) with currency holdings.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-monetary-base-high-powered-money> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''monetary base (high-powered money)''' ;
  skos:definition '''Currency in circulation plus bank reserves; directly controlled by the central bank.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-reserve-ratio> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''reserve ratio''' ;
  skos:definition '''The fraction of deposits that banks hold as reserves; can be required (required reserve ratio) or held voluntarily (excess reserves).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-open-market-operations> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''open market operations''' ;
  skos:definition '''Central bank purchases or sales of government securities to expand or contract the monetary base.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-nominal-interest-rate> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''nominal interest rate''' ;
  skos:definition '''The interest rate expressed in monetary terms, unadjusted for inflation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-real-interest-rate> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''real interest rate''' ;
  skos:definition '''The nominal interest rate minus the inflation rate (or expected inflation): r ≈ i - π.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-quantity-theory-of-money> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''quantity theory of money''' ;
  skos:definition '''The theory that the price level is proportional to the money supply: MV = PY, implying inflation equals money growth minus output growth.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-seigniorage> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''seigniorage''' ;
  skos:definition '''Revenue earned by the government from money creation; the real value of resources acquired by printing money.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-taylor-rule> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Taylor rule''' ;
  skos:definition '''A monetary policy guideline: i = r* + π + α(π - π*) + β(Y - Y*); the central bank raises interest rates when inflation exceeds target or output exceeds potential.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-velocity-of-money> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''velocity of money''' ;
  skos:definition '''The average number of times a dollar is spent on final goods in a period: V = PY/M.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-quantity-equation> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Quantity equation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''M·V = P·Y  (MV = PQ)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-quantity-theory-of-inflation> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Quantity theory of inflation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''π = ΔM/M - ΔY/Y (assuming constant V)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-fisher-equation> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Fisher equation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''i = r + π^e  (nominal rate = real rate + expected inflation)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-fisher-effect> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Fisher effect''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''A 1 percentage point increase in expected inflation raises the nominal interest rate by 1 percentage point, leaving the real rate unchanged.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-money-multiplier-simple> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Money multiplier (simple)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''ΔDeposits = (1/rr) · ΔReserves;  m = 1/rr''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-money-multiplier-with-currency-drain> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Money multiplier (with currency drain)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''m = (1 + c)/(rr + c)  where c = currency-to-deposit ratio''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-taylor-rule> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Taylor rule''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''i = r* + π + 0.5(π - π*) + 0.5(Y - Y*)/Y*''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-seigniorage> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Seigniorage''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Seigniorage = (ΔM/P) = (ΔM/M)·(M/P) = π·(M/P) in steady state''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-money-banking-and-inflation-hyperinflation-mechanism> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Hyperinflation mechanism''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Large fiscal deficits monetized by central bank → rapid money growth → accelerating inflation → reduced real money demand → further price increases (Sargent-Wallace).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-money-banking-and-inflation> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Unemployment and Labor Markets''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-economics> ;
