<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> skos:scopeNote '''Types of unemployment: frictional, structural, cyclical; Natural rate of unemployment; Labor force and participation rate; Okun's law; Phillips curve: short-run and long-run; Expectations-augmented Phillips curve; Wage rigidity and efficiency wages; Job search and matching models; NAIRU''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-unemployment-rate> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''unemployment rate''' ;
  skos:definition '''The percentage of the labor force that is not employed but actively seeking work: u = U/(U+E) × 100%.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-labor-force> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''labor force''' ;
  skos:definition '''The sum of employed and unemployed persons who are of working age and actively seeking employment.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-frictional-unemployment> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''frictional unemployment''' ;
  skos:definition '''Temporary unemployment arising from the time taken to match workers with suitable jobs; reflects normal labor market turnover.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-structural-unemployment> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''structural unemployment''' ;
  skos:definition '''Unemployment caused by a mismatch between workers' skills and the skills required by available jobs, often due to technological change or sectoral shifts.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-cyclical-unemployment> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''cyclical unemployment''' ;
  skos:definition '''Unemployment caused by insufficient aggregate demand during economic downturns; the gap between actual and natural unemployment.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-natural-rate-of-unemployment-u> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''natural rate of unemployment (u*)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The unemployment rate consistent with stable inflation; equal to frictional plus structural unemployment.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-nairu> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''NAIRU''' ;
  skos:definition '''Non-Accelerating Inflation Rate of Unemployment; the unemployment rate at which inflation is stable; synonymous with natural rate in standard models.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-phillips-curve> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Phillips curve''' ;
  skos:definition '''An empirical inverse relationship between unemployment and inflation; the short-run Phillips curve shifts with expected inflation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-okun-s-law> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Okun's law''' ;
  skos:definition '''An empirical relationship between output gaps and cyclical unemployment: a 1 percentage point rise in unemployment corresponds to approximately a 2% fall in output below potential.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-efficiency-wage> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''efficiency wage''' ;
  skos:definition '''A wage above the market-clearing level set by firms to boost worker productivity, reduce turnover, or attract better workers; can cause unemployment.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-labor-force-participation-rate> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''labor force participation rate''' ;
  skos:definition '''The percentage of the civilian non-institutional population that is in the labor force.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-unemployment-rate> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Unemployment rate''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''u = U / (U + E) = U / LF''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-labor-force-participation-rate> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Labor force participation rate''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''LFPR = LF / Working-age population''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-okun-s-law> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Okun's law''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''ΔY/Y ≈ -2 × Δu  (or: Y - Y* ≈ -2(u - u*))''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-short-run-phillips-curve> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Short-run Phillips curve''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''π = π^e - α(u - u*);  inflation rises when u < u*''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-expectations-augmented-phillips-curve> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Expectations-augmented Phillips curve''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''π = π^e + β(Y - Y*) - α(u - u*);  adaptive expectations: π^e = π_{t-1}''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-long-run-phillips-curve> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Long-run Phillips curve''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Vertical at u = u* (NAIRU); in long run, expected inflation = actual inflation, no trade-off between π and u.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-steady-state-unemployment-flows> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Steady-state unemployment (flows)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''u* = s / (s + f);  s = job separation rate, f = job finding rate''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets-sacrifice-ratio> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Sacrifice ratio''' ;
  skos:definition '''Sacrifice ratio = (cumulative % output loss) / (percentage point reduction in inflation); measures cost of disinflation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-unemployment-and-labor-markets> ;
  kcc:canonType '''definition''' ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Economic Growth: Solow Model''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-economics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> skos:scopeNote '''Solow growth model setup; Steady-state capital and output; Golden rule of capital accumulation; Convergence: conditional and absolute; Total factor productivity and the Solow residual; Human capital (Mankiw-Romer-Weil extension); Endogenous growth theory (Romer model basics); Growth accounting''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-solow-model> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Solow model''' ;
  skos:definition '''A neoclassical growth model in which the long-run growth rate is determined by exogenous technological progress; capital accumulation drives transitional dynamics.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-capital-per-worker-k> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''capital per worker (k)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The capital-labor ratio: k = K/L; the central state variable in the Solow model.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-steady-state> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''steady state''' ;
  skos:definition '''The long-run equilibrium in the Solow model where capital per worker is constant (investment equals depreciation plus population growth).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-depreciation> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''depreciation''' ;
  skos:definition '''The rate at which capital wears out or becomes obsolete, typically denoted δ.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-golden-rule-capital-stock> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''golden rule capital stock''' ;
  skos:definition '''The steady-state capital-per-worker level that maximizes consumption per worker: MPK = δ + n + g.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-total-factor-productivity-tfp> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''total factor productivity (TFP)''' ;
  skos:definition '''The portion of output growth not explained by input growth; a measure of technological efficiency: A in Y = A·F(K,L).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-solow-residual> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Solow residual''' ;
  skos:definition '''The empirical measure of TFP growth, calculated as output growth minus the weighted sum of capital and labor growth.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-conditional-convergence> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''conditional convergence''' ;
  skos:definition '''The tendency for economies with similar structural parameters to converge to the same steady state; poorer economies grow faster given identical fundamentals.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-endogenous-growth> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''endogenous growth''' ;
  skos:definition '''Growth theory in which the long-run growth rate is explained by the model itself (e.g., through R&D, human capital, or knowledge spillovers) rather than exogenous TFP.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-growth-accounting> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''growth accounting''' ;
  skos:definition '''A technique decomposing output growth into contributions from capital, labor, and TFP: ΔY/Y = α·ΔK/K + (1-α)·ΔL/L + ΔA/A.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-solow-production-function-intensive-form> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Solow production function (intensive form)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''y = f(k) = A·k^α  (Cobb-Douglas); where y = Y/L, k = K/L''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-capital-accumulation-equation> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Capital accumulation equation''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Δk = s·f(k) - (δ + n + g)·k''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-steady-state-condition> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Steady-state condition''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''s·f(k*) = (δ + n + g)·k*  ⟹  k* is the steady-state capital per effective worker''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-steady-state-output-per-worker-cobb-douglas> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Steady-state output per worker (Cobb-Douglas)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''k* = (s/(δ+n+g))^{1/(1-α)};  y* = A·(k*)^α''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-golden-rule-condition> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Golden rule condition''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''MPK = δ + n + g  ⟺  α·f(k_GR)/k_GR = δ + n + g''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-growth-accounting-solow-residual> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Growth accounting (Solow residual)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''ΔA/A = ΔY/Y - α·ΔK/K - (1-α)·ΔL/L''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-long-run-growth-rate> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Long-run growth rate''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''In Solow model, long-run growth of Y per worker = g (rate of technological progress); growth of Y = g + n.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-convergence-prediction> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Convergence prediction''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Economies with lower k relative to k* grow faster; speed of convergence ≈ (1-α)(δ+n+g).''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-economic-growth-solow-model-ak-endogenous-growth-model> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''AK (endogenous) growth model''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Y = AK; constant MPK → no diminishing returns → sustained growth without exogenous TFP.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-economic-growth-solow-model> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Fiscal and Monetary Policy''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-economics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> skos:scopeNote '''Fiscal policy: discretionary and automatic stabilizers; Government budget constraint and debt dynamics; Ricardian equivalence; Monetary policy rules vs. discretion; Inflation targeting; Central bank independence; Policy lags (recognition, implementation, effect); Crowding out and fiscal multiplier in open economy; Zero lower bound and unconventional monetary policy''' .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-discretionary-fiscal-policy> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''discretionary fiscal policy''' ;
  skos:definition '''Deliberate changes in government spending or taxes to stabilize the economy, requiring explicit policy decisions.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-automatic-stabilizers> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''automatic stabilizers''' ;
  skos:definition '''Budget mechanisms that automatically increase spending or reduce taxes in recessions (e.g., unemployment insurance, progressive tax) without new legislation.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-ricardian-equivalence> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Ricardian equivalence''' ;
  skos:definition '''The proposition that tax cuts financed by debt have no effect on aggregate demand because rational consumers save the tax cut in anticipation of future higher taxes.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-government-budget-constraint> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''government budget constraint''' ;
  skos:definition '''G - T = ΔB + ΔM; the government deficit must be financed by issuing bonds or money.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-primary-deficit> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''primary deficit''' ;
  skos:definition '''The government deficit excluding interest payments on existing debt: G - T (excluding interest).''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-debt-to-gdp-ratio-dynamics> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''debt-to-GDP ratio dynamics''' ;
  skos:definition '''The change in the debt-to-GDP ratio depends on the primary deficit and the difference between the real interest rate and the growth rate.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-inflation-targeting> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''inflation targeting''' ;
  skos:definition '''A monetary policy framework in which the central bank announces an explicit inflation target and adjusts policy instruments to achieve it.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-time-inconsistency> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''time inconsistency''' ;
  skos:definition '''The tendency for policymakers to deviate from previously announced optimal plans once the private sector has formed expectations; motivates central bank independence and rules.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-quantitative-easing-qe> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''quantitative easing (QE)''' ;
  skos:definition '''An unconventional monetary policy in which the central bank purchases large quantities of assets (beyond short-term government bonds) to lower long-term interest rates and stimulate the economy.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#term-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-crowding-out> a kcc:GlossaryTerm ;
  skos:prefLabel '''crowding out''' ;
  skos:definition '''The reduction in private investment resulting from government borrowing that raises interest rates; reduces the effectiveness of fiscal expansion.''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
  skos:inScheme kcc:CanonScheme .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-government-budget-constraint> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Government budget constraint''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''G + r·B = T + ΔB + ΔM/P  (spending + interest = revenue + bond issuance + seigniorage)''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-debt-to-gdp-dynamics> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Debt-to-GDP dynamics''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Δ(B/Y) = (G-T)/Y + (r-g)·(B/Y);  debt ratio rises if r > g and primary deficit > 0''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-fiscal-multiplier-closed-economy-simple> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Fiscal multiplier (closed economy, simple)''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''ΔY = ΔG/(1-MPC);  or  ΔY = (-MPC/(1-MPC))·ΔT''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-ricardian-equivalence-condition> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Ricardian equivalence condition''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''If consumers are forward-looking and face perfect capital markets, a bond-financed tax cut does not affect consumption: ΔC = 0.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-taylor-rule> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Taylor rule''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''i_t = r* + π_t + α(π_t - π*) + β(Y_t - Y_t*)/Y_t*;  typically α=0.5, β=0.5''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''equation''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-monetary-policy-transmission-channels> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Monetary policy transmission channels''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Interest rate channel → investment; credit channel → bank lending; exchange rate channel → net exports; asset price channel → wealth/consumption.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-zero-lower-bound-constraint> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Zero lower bound constraint''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''i ≥ 0; when i = 0, conventional monetary policy loses effectiveness; QE, forward guidance, and negative rates are alternatives.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#formula-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy-barro-ricardo-tax-smoothing> a kcc:Formula ;
  rdfs:label '''Barro-Ricardo tax smoothing''' ;
  math:hasStatement '''Optimally, taxes should be smoothed over time (like permanent income); temporary spending increases should be debt-financed.''' ;
  kcc:canonType '''principle''' ;
  dct:subject <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-fiscal-and-monetary-policy> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext .
<https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#topic-economics-econometrics-ols-and-regression> a kcc:Topic ;
  skos:prefLabel '''Econometrics: OLS and Regression''' ;
  kcc:level '''undergrad''' ;
  skos:broader <https://socioprophet.github.io/ontogenesis/domains/knowledge-commons-canon#domain-economics> ;
  kcc:inKnowledgeContext kcc:CanonKnowledgeContext ;
